  {"a":"ornn","b":"aatrox","win":["Skill","Skill","Aatrox","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"His sweetspot Q knockups and W chain-pull come fully online — this is his cleanest kill window before your W shield stabilizes you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R gives you a long-range double knock-up that beats his R all-in — reactivate it into your own Q-pillar for a guaranteed E-Q stun chain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"A Heartsteel/Sunfire spike turns you into a durable W-poke bully who tanks his drain trades and chunks him with percent-HP Brittle."},{"when":"Lvl 13","text":"Master Craftsman upgrades your and your team's legendaries to Masterwork — the effective gold lead makes his single-target duel irrelevant."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his level 3 sweetspot-Q window by farming with your own Q line until W comes up","Land E into a Q-pillar (or your R elemental) to knock him up and trigger Brittle for amplified burst","Reach 6 and your first tank item to flip the lane into a durable W-poke bully"],"foe":["Catch you at level 3 with sweetspot-Q knockup into W chain-pull before your shield exists","Hit you with passive-healed drain trades to win extended fights and stack his R uptime","Bait your E-Q whiff with a dash, then all-in with R combat stats once your CC is down"]},"early":"Levels 1 and 2 are rough for both of us — I have no shield, no combo, and I'm mana-starved, while his sweetspot Q and chain-pull aren't fully threatening yet either, so I just farm with the head of my Q line and don't step into his W pull. Level 3 is his window, not mine: once he has Q-W-E he can sweetspot-knockup into a W chain-pull and drain a big chunk before my W (Bellows Breath) exists to shield it. Hold the wave, take CS at max range, and don't contest a trade until I have W's unstoppable percent-HP poke to answer his passive heal.","mid":"This is where the lane turns. With a second point in my combo I can punish any overextension by dropping a Q-pillar and dashing E into it for a knock-up that triggers Brittle, then W-burst him through his drain. Bait his sweetspot Q — once it whiffs he has no answer to my unstoppable W. At 6 my R is the trump card: the charging elemental double-knocks him up and I can reactivate it to redirect for a second, larger knock-up, which flat-out beats his R all-in since his combat-stat steroid does nothing while he's airborne.","late":"Once I hit my first tank item I'm a W-poke bully who eats his drain trades and out-durables the duel, and his extended-trade win condition stops mattering. At 13 my passive upgrades my and my team's legendaries into Masterwork versions — that's an effective gold lead five players wide, and it makes his single-target presence irrelevant. He can still drain-tank a sidelane, so don't 1v1 him forever with no items; instead group, chain my E-Q-R CC into Brittle, and let the teamfight ceiling close it out.","whys":["He has no level-1 threat without his combo, but neither do I with no shield or mana — we both just last-hit and set the wave.","His sweetspot Q isn't online yet and my W still doesn't exist, so it stays a farming standoff where neither of us can commit.","At 3 his sweetspot-Q knockup into W chain-pull and passive heal out-trade me before my Bellows Breath shield is up to answer it.","A second combo point lets me E into a Q-pillar for a Brittle knock-up, so trades go even once I can punish his whiffed Q.","My R double knock-up wins the all-in outright — his R combat steroid does nothing while he's airborne in my elemental.","My Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes me tank his drain trades while W chunks him with percent-HP Brittle.","Master Craftsman Masterwork upgrades hand my whole team an effective gold lead that drowns out his single-target duel."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"akali","win":["Ornn","Skill","Skill","Skill","Akali","Akali","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Akali has no Q energy refund or passive ring stacked yet, so your auto-and-step-back beats her single Q poke before she has shroud to escape."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Akali R's two-part dash hops your telegraphed E-Q and the execute second cast bursts you through your W shield — her hardest all-in window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Akali's first AP item plus W Twilight Shroud lets her dodge your E-Q knock-up combo inside the smoke and reset the trade — respect the shroud timer."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your level-13 Masterwork upgrades and Heartsteel stacks make you near-unkillable for her — you become a frontline she can't burst through."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up before she can W into shroud to dodge it","Use W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield to tank her R burst and trade back","Reach 2+ items and your level-13 Masterwork upgrades so her single-target burst can't kill you"],"foe":["W Twilight Shroud the instant you E so the knock-up whiffs and she's untargetable","Hold R's two-part dash to hop your E-Q telegraph and execute you through your shield","Farm safely to 2 AP items where her shuriken-and-shroud combo out-bursts your tank stats"]},"early":"Akali is shovable and energy-starved at level 1, and you actually out-poke her opening Q here — auto her and step back before she gets shroud online, since she has no W escape yet. Your W (Bellows Breath) is unstoppable and shields, so a few percent-HP exhales trade up against her squishy early frame. Don't waste E chasing into her Q range; just hold it for when she steps up to last-hit so you can E-Q-pillar her into the wall.","mid":"From level 2 to 5 this is a skill lane — she has her shuriken dash (E) and W Twilight Shroud, and a good Akali drops the smoke the moment you commit your E, making your knock-up whiff and turning her untargetable. Bait the shroud: feint your dash, let her burn W or back off, then E into your Q pillar for the real stun. At 6 she takes over — her R's two-part dash skips your telegraphed E-Q and the second cast executes you through your W shield, so don't all-in on her ult; W to blunt the burst and disengage.","late":"She owns the mid-game once she has her first AP item and shroud — she dodges your whole combo inside the smoke and bursts you on her timer, so play for farm and don't face-check her in the shroud. But this flips hard your way late: at level 13 your free Masterwork upgrades and a stacked Heartsteel/Sunfire frontline make you a target her single-target burst simply cannot kill. Anchor teamfights, chain E-Q and R double knock-up onto her, and let your team punish her once she's blown R trying to reach a carry.","whys":["You out-poke her single early Q and she has no shroud escape yet, so your auto-and-step-back trades beat her at level 1.","She gets her shuriken dash (E) but you have W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale — it's even as both of you are still setting up.","Your Q-W lets you trade, but her W Twilight Shroud can make your E-Q knock-up whiff inside the smoke — genuinely skill-dependent.","You get a second combo point but a good Akali shrouds your E commit and resets, keeping it even on who reads who.","Akali's R two-part dash hops your telegraphed E-Q and the execute bursts you through your W shield — she owns the 6 all-in.","Her first AP item plus shroud lets her dodge your full combo and burst you on her timer, out-itemizing your single-target presence.","Your level-13 Masterwork upgrades and Heartsteel frontline make you near-unkillable for her single-target burst — you reclaim the duel as the anchor."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"akshan","win":["Skill","Akshan","Akshan","Akshan","Akshan","Akshan","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You have no shield and no combo yet, so eat his Q poke and just last-hit at max Q range until you get W."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q wall is your only real kill threat — bait his E grapple into a wall and ult him before he can swing out."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus W's percent-HP exhale lets you tank his poke and survive his all-in, but he can still kite your E-Q."},{"when":"Late","text":"Once you hit 13 and free Masterwork upgrades, your team value and durability beat his single-target poke in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your own Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then W-exhale Brittle for max-HP burst","Survive his Q/W poke with W's shield and reach your Level 6 R all-in window","Scale to 13 for free Masterwork upgrades and become the teamfight anchor he can't kill"],"foe":["Poke you with Q and W from outside your W/E range and never commit","Use E grapple to dodge your telegraphed E-Q knock-up and reset spacing","Roam with camouflage and his passive revive to snowball other lanes off your slow shove"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are miserable for me here — I have no shield, no combo, and I'm mana-starved while Akshan pokes me with Q and W from range I can't answer. Don't walk up to trade; last-hit at the tip of my Q and accept the chip. Once I hit 3 and have W, I can finally exhale percent-HP back at him and shield an all-in, but he just grapples out on E and keeps kiting.","mid":"My only kill pressure is E-into-Q-pillar — I dash, hit my own magma wall, and knock him up, then W-exhale Brittle for the burst. The problem is his E grapple dodges my telegraphed dash unless I trap him against a wall first. At 6, R adds a long-range double knock-up; bait his swing, ult, then E-Q. If he plays back and just farm-pokes, I can't force it — he edges these levels.","late":"This is where I take it back. By 13 my free Masterwork upgrades give my whole team an effective gold lead, and I'm a near-unkillable anchor his single-target poke can't burn through. In a fight my E-Q-R chain locks him down before he revives away. Don't chase his roams 1v1 — group, soak his poke on my shield, and win the 5v5 where my upgrades and CC outweigh his kiting.","whys":["Akshan is a ranged poke skirmisher and I have no shield or combo at 1 — but he can't all-in me either, so we just trade farm.","He pokes me down with Q and W from outside my range while I have no W to answer yet.","Even with W online he grapples out of my E-Q on his E, kiting my percent-HP exhale before I can land Brittle.","His Q/W poke chips me faster than I can punish, and his E spacing denies my E-into-pillar knock-up.","His own kit threatens me through 6 — if he sidesteps my R-E-Q he just resets and pokes, and his roam pressure off camouflage hurts more than my ult.","His first-item poke and waveclear let him keep me on the back foot and roam with his revive passive while I farm.","At 13 my free Masterwork upgrades and W shield make me the durable teamfight anchor his single-target poke can't kill, and my E-Q-R locks him down."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"ambessa","win":["Skill","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Once you have Q and W (Bellows Breath), your unstoppable percent-HP exhale lets you trade back through her W damage instead of just eating it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up finally pins a champion who otherwise dashes out of every E-Q — your one clean kill window before items."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots make you tanky enough to survive her full dash combo and W burst, but she is still the one dictating engages."},{"when":"Late","text":"At 2+ items and your level-13 Masterwork upgrades, you out-durability her single-target combo and become the teamfight anchor she can't kill."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into a Q pillar (or her own body on terrain) to knock her up and trigger Brittle before she dashes away","Use W's unstoppable cast to trade through her W damage and shield her dash-in burst","Stall to 2+ items and Masterwork upgrades where your durability outlasts her combo"],"foe":["Weave her dashes around your telegraphed E so the Q-pillar knock-up whiffs","Stack her chain CC and W damage in repeated short trades while you're mana-starved early","Snowball levels 2-6 before your R and tank items come online"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are miserable — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-hungry, so just last-hit and don't contest her. The danger is her dash-heavy combo and W damage in repeated short trades you can't answer yet. Once you hit 3 and have Q plus W (Bellows Breath), you can finally trade back: W is unstoppable and deals percent max-HP, so cast it as she dashes in to blunt her burst and chip her. Don't throw a blind E hoping to wall her — she weaves around skillshots and you'll just be on cooldown when she re-engages.","mid":"This is where she's strongest and you're surviving, not winning. Her mobility lets her dodge your E-into-Q-pillar setup, so don't telegraph it — bait a dash first, then E into your own Q wall (or any terrain) to land the knock-up and detonate Brittle. Level 6 is your one real kill window: R's double knock-up pins her where her dashes can't save her, so set up an all-in or gank on it. Outside of that, she dictates engages with her chain CC, so play around your wave and your jungler.","late":"Your time finally comes. At 2+ items, and especially after your level-13 Master Craftsman upgrades turn your team's legendaries into Masterworks, you out-durability her single-target combo — she can dash in and dump W damage and you simply don't die. Stop trying to 1v1 her in a side lane where her dashes and CC reset; group, and let your E-Q-R chain CC into Brittle anchor the teamfight. The effective gold lead from your free upgrades is the win condition, not the lane.","whys":["You're one of the weakest level-1s with no shield or combo, but she's still setting up too — neither of you commits, so it's a Skill farm.","She has her dash combo and W damage online while you have one ability and no mana cushion to answer short trades.","Her mobility lets her weave around your telegraphed E, so the Q-pillar knock-up whiffs and she out-trades you with chain CC.","She punishes you in repeated trades with W damage faster than your two-point combo can set up a knock-up.","Even with R's double knock-up threatening, she can bait it with a dash and her sustained combo edges the all-in before your items.","Her dash burst still beats your first tank item in a straight 1v1 — you're durable but not yet the wall she can't kill.","At 2+ items plus your level-13 Masterwork upgrades you out-durability her single-target combo and anchor fights she can't win."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"aurora","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) percent-HP poke and shield punish her squishy early body before she has Q poke stacks online."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"E into your own Q pillar knocks her up — if she E-blinks late she eats the full Brittle-amplified stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R's double knock-up is a long-range gap-close she cannot blink out of once the second ram redirects through her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots make you a durable W-poke bully who shrugs off her Q-W combo damage."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into a Q-pillar wall to knock her up and detonate Brittle with W before she can E-blink away","Use W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale to out-poke her squishy body and blunt her root-burst all-ins","Catch her with R's double knock-up at 6 so she can't blink the second redirect"],"foe":["Hold her E blink for your E-Q telegraph and reposition the instant your dash starts","Stack Q poke and W spirit zoning to chip you down from outside your W/E range","Land her root to land her full Q-W burst combo while your CC is on cooldown"]},"early":"Aurora is squishy and her Q poke does not really come online turn-1, so Levels 1-2 are yours — step up and W (Bellows Breath) her through minions for unstoppable percent-HP damage plus a shield, and she has nothing to trade back that beats your sustain. Do not throw a naked Q at her; it telegraphs your E follow-up and she will just E-blink. Bait her into staying for a trade and you win the body-on-body exchange every time before her poke pattern matures.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are about the E-Q trap: dash E into your own Q magma pillar to knock her up, then W to detonate Brittle for amplified burst. The catch is her E blink — if she has it up she dodges your telegraph, so this stage is genuinely skill-on-skill until 6. At 6 the math flips hard: R summons a charging knock-up and you redirect it for a second, longer ram she physically cannot blink out of once it's traveling through her. That's your kill window — bait her root, eat it, then R.","late":"You don't fall off this one the way you do versus hard scalers — Aurora stays a squishy skirmish-mage, and your first tank item plus W-poke makes you a lane bully she can't shove off. In teamfights your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your R double knock-up catch her even through her W exile and E blinks; she's exactly the kind of squishy your engage deletes. Keep landing E-Q onto her and she never gets to play the kite-and-poke game she wants.","whys":["She has no Q poke stacks online turn-1 and your W percent-HP exhale plus shield out-trades her squishy level-1 body.","Still no real poke from her — your W unstoppable damage chips her down with no risk while she just farms.","Even skill: your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up wins the trade, but a held E blink lets her dodge the telegraph.","She can blink your E-Q if she plays it perfectly, but a mistimed blink eats the full Brittle stun — pure mechanics.","R's double knock-up redirect is a long-range catch she cannot blink the second ram out of — your kill window.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots make you a W-poke bully who tanks her full Q-W combo and shrugs it off.","She stays squishy with no hard-scaling reclaim — your R engage and Masterwork upgrades delete her in fights."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"camille","win":["Skill","Camille","Camille","Camille","Skill","Camille","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Camille's Q true-damage proc plus E hookshot stun out-trades you before your W shield is online — give up CS rather than fight."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up answers her R isolation — if she ults you in, E-Q wall her into a stun and reverse the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sheen/Eclipse Camille spikes hard — her Q proc and W heal let her dive your W cooldown, so trade only when Bellows Breath is up."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"She out-scales the duel: her E wall-dash and R isolation let her catch you alone, but your free Masterwork upgrades flip the teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 6 even on CS, then E-Q wall her R isolation into a knock-up and W-Brittle her down","Use your magma pillar (Q terrain) to deny her E hookshot grip points and her wall-dash escapes","Group and end through teamfights where your Masterwork upgrades and double knock-up R outvalue her 1v1 R"],"foe":["Stack Q true-damage procs and W heal to win every short trade before your W shield comes up","Use E hookshot stun and R isolation to catch you out and duel you where your team cannot help","Scale to two items and splitpush, forcing 1v1s her wall-dash mobility wins"]},"early":"Camille owns the first trades — her Q true-damage proc and W cone heal out-sustain you, and you have no shield until Level 3, no combo, and mana problems. Do not contest CS in her E hookshot range; she dashes in, stuns, and procs Q before you can W back. Last-hit with the tip of your Q line and accept the poke. Once W (Bellows Breath) is up at 3 you can finally answer an all-in with unstoppable percent-HP fire, but she still edges the short trades — respect the Q proc timer.","mid":"Levels 4-5 still favor her: a pre-item Camille bursts with Q resets and heals through your W. Your real swing is 6. When she E-hookshots in or R-isolates you, you are not helpless — E into your own Q pillar knocks her up, W applies Brittle, and your R's double knock-up cancels her wall-dash escape and the R cylinder she trapped you in. Bait her E wall-dash, then E-Q the instant she commits. If she plays it safe, just farm even and don't walk into a hookshot grip point.","late":"She out-scales the straight duel — at two items her Q true damage, W heal, and R isolation let her catch you splitpushing and win the 1v1, so don't get caught alone with your R down. But this is your game in the 5v5: your free Masterwork upgrades give your whole team a gold lead, and your E-Q-wall plus double knock-up R chain CC in fights she can only ever 1v1. Force grouped objectives, don't side-lane against her, and let your team punish a Camille who flanks in alone.","whys":["Camille is also a weak level-1, but her Q proc edges your shieldless, combo-less start — deny her last-hits and set up the lane.","Her Q true-damage proc plus E hookshot stun out-trade you before W is online — don't contest CS in dash range.","With W up you can answer all-ins, but her Q resets and W heal still win the short trades — farm and wait for 6.","A pre-item Camille bursts through your W shield with Q true damage; force her to use E wall-dash before you commit.","Your R double knock-up cancels her R isolation and E escape — E into your Q pillar to knock her up and W-Brittle her down.","Her Sheen/Eclipse spike lets her dive your W cooldown — only trade with Bellows Breath up or she heals it back.","Your free Masterwork upgrades and double knock-up R win the teamfight even as her wall-dash and R isolation out-duel you 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Skill","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Cass has no Twin Fang stacks yet — soak her Q poison with hard shoves so you hit Level 3 W before her DPS ramps."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up plus W Brittle is your one clean all-in window before her items, but her R face-stun cancels it if you eat it mid-dash."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots make you a W-poke lane bully, but her Grounding W on your E-Q dash is the threat that shuts the engage down."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Full-AP Cass kites with passive move speed and grounds every dash — she out-DPSes your single-target presence, so this is her window."}],"wants":{"you":["Hard-shove waves to deny her farm and crash before she can free-poke you with Q poison","Bait her R face-stun, then land E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and W Brittle for the kill before 6 fades","End the lane on your Level 6 / first-item spike before her AP items make her uncatchable"],"foe":["Ground your E dash and Q-pillar engage with her W so you can never close distance","Stack Twin Fang poison ticks and kite with no-boots passive move speed","Scale to 2+ items where her sustained poison DPS melts you through armor stacking"]},"early":"Cassiopeia is mana-starved and stuck shoving for her own Twin Fang stacks early, and you are an even weaker Level 1, so just farm and soak her Q poison rather than walking up. The danger is her W grounding — it cancels your E dash mid-flight, so do NOT throw out E-Q to engage at Levels 1-2 or you'll get grounded and poisoned for free. Hard-shove the wave with W's percent-HP poke once you hit 3 and look to crash before her sustained DPS ramps.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your only realistic kill window, but it's narrow against her. Bait her R face-stun first — if you eat it mid-E it cancels your whole combo — then E into your own Q-pillar for the knock-up, follow with W for Brittle, and burst her before her poison out-trades you. At 6 your R double knock-up can lock her through a single Grounding W, but if she saves W for your dash she simply kites the elemental and out-poisons you, so commit only when her W is down.","late":"This is where she takes over and there's no sugarcoating it — full-AP Cass grounds every E dash and Q-pillar engage you have, kites on her no-boots passive move speed, and her sustained Twin Fang poison ignores your armor stacking entirely. You don't win the straight 1v1 here. Your value flips to being a teamfight anchor with free Masterwork upgrades — let your team body her while you R-engage from fog where she can't ground you, and never face a side-lane 1v1 into a fed Cassiopeia.","whys":["Cass has no Twin Fang stacks and is as weak as you at Level 1 — just last-hit and don't walk into Q poison range.","Her Q poison plus early Grounding W out-trades you before your combo exists — she edges the level-2 poke war.","She free-poisons you while you wait on your W, and her W grounds any early E engage you try.","She out-DPSes your trades with stacked Twin Fang and kites your telegraphed E-Q with passive move speed.","Even your R all-in window is contestable — her R face-stun and Grounding W can blank the double knock-up.","Her first AP item ramps her poison DPS faster than your tank spike can punish a kiting, grounding mage.","Full-AP Cass grounds every dash, kites freely, and melts your armor stacking with percent-poison DPS."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"chogath","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Cho'Gath","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath), its unstoppable percent-HP exhale out-pokes a Cho'Gath who has to walk into melee range to land Q knockup."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun chains Brittle for a kill, but this is Cho's first Feast window — a stacked R can true-damage execute you if you fight low."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a durable W-poke bully; force trades before Cho stacks Feast HP."},{"when":"Late","text":"At 2+ items Cho out-tanks you and his R is true-damage percent execute that ignores your armor — stop dueling and play the teamfight anchor."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 W (Bellows Breath) to poke his max-HP with unstoppable percent damage he can't kite","Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up-stun and detonate Brittle with W or autos","Force trades before he Feast-stacks, then convert your 13 Masterwork upgrade lead in fights"],"foe":["Stack Feast (R) charges off your minions and any kill to inflate his max HP","Land his Q knockup to set up a free W silence and harass window","Survive to 2+ items where his true-damage R execute ignores your armor stacking"]},"early":"Cho'Gath has to step into melee range to threaten his Q knockup, and that's exactly where my W (Bellows Breath) punishes him — it's unstoppable, shields me, and chunks a percent of his max HP while applying Brittle. Levels 1-2 I'm mana-starved and weak like always, so I just last-hit and respect his Q-into-W silence combo if I'm caught out of position. From 3 onward my W out-trades his harass and I start eating his stacks off the wave before he can Feast freely.","mid":"This is my window. With a second point in my combo I can E into a Q pillar for a knock-up-stun, then W or auto to pop Brittle for real burst — Cho is big and slow with no dash to dodge the telegraph. At 6 my R adds a long-range double knock-up that wins the all-in, but be honest about his 6: if his Feast R is stacked and I'm low, that true-damage percent execute can flip the fight, so don't all-in below half.","late":"Cho out-scales me as a pure tank — he keeps stacking Feast HP and his R is a true-damage percent execute that laughs at my armor. I stop trying to solo him at 2+ items. My value shifts to the teamfight: at 13 my free Masterwork upgrades hand my whole team an effective gold lead, and my E-Q-R CC chain catches his whole backline. Anchor the fight, don't duel the Cho.","whys":["He has to enter melee for Q knockup while you're just farming — neither of you wants to commit, but you're never behind here.","His Q-W is his only real harass and you can sidestep the slow Q line; keep last-hitting and don't feed early Feast stacks.","W (Bellows Breath) gives unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield his melee Q can't answer — you start out-trading.","E into your Q pillar knocks him up and stuns; Brittle detonation bursts a Cho who has no dash to dodge it.","This is his Feast spike — a stacked R is a true-damage percent execute that can flip an all-in, so he edges the kill window if you fight low.","Your first-item Heartsteel/Sunfire plus W-poke makes you a tankier lane bully than a still-stacking Cho.","He out-tanks you and his true-damage R ignores your armor — it's even at best because your free Masterwork upgrades and CC chain keep your teamfight ceiling high."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"darius","win":["Darius","Darius","Darius","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Darius owns the early all-in — his E pull plus passive bleed stacks shred you before your W shield exists, so just farm with Q-tip from max range."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale and a shield blunt his Apprehend pull and let you Brittle-poke him as you stabilize."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) plus your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up chains CC he can't answer — your first window to flip an all-in and win the lane."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 plus a tank item make you the near-unkillable teamfight anchor while Darius's single-target R execute stops one-shotting you."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 with safe Q-tip farming until W (Bellows Breath) gives you a shield and percent-HP poke","Land E into your own Q-pillar for the knock-up, then W-Brittle to amplify the follow-up","Reach 6 and your tank item, then flip every Darius all-in with R double knock-up"],"foe":["Land Apprehend (E) to pull you in and start Hemorrhage bleed stacks before you have a shield","All-in you levels 1-9 where his empowered Q and bleed out-trade your mana-starved early kit","Snowball off an early kill before your R and Masterwork upgrades make you unkillable"]},"early":"Darius owns the first three levels and you can't fight back — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, while his E pull drags you into empowered Q and Hemorrhage bleed stacks that out-trade anything you have. Do NOT walk up to last-hit in his E range; farm with the tip of your Q from max distance and eat a little CS loss. Your only goal here is to reach level 3 and W (Bellows Breath) so its shield and unstoppable percent-HP exhale give you something to trade with and answer his pull.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even out as your second combo point lands — bait his E pull, then E into your own Q-pillar to knock him up and W-Brittle through it for a real trade he can't bleed his way out of. At 6 you take over: R (Call of the Forge God) adds a long-range double knock-up that wins the all-in his empowered Q used to own, and you can chain it into your E-Q stun. Hold W until he commits his pull so the unstoppable eats his all-in, then punish.","late":"You flip this lane for good once itemized — a tank item plus your Masterwork upgrades at 13 make you the near-unkillable anchor, and Darius's R true-damage execute stops being a one-shot when you stack health. Don't duel him isolated under his turret where his bleed and reset R snowball; instead group, chain your R-into-E-Q knock-up to lock him in a fight, and let your free item lead carry teamfights. He stays a threat in a straight 1v1, so never give him an isolated pick.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo, and no mana — Darius's E pull into bleed stacks shreds you, so just farm with Q-tip and concede the level.","Still no W shield to answer his Apprehend pull, and his empowered Q out-trades your mana-starved kit — keep last-hitting from range.","Even with W (Bellows Breath) online his bleed plus E all-in still edges your shield trade — stabilize, don't fight.","Your second combo point lets you E into your Q-pillar for a knock-up, baiting his pull to make the trade genuinely even.","R (Call of the Forge God) adds a double knock-up that wins the all-in, and your E-Q stun chains CC his empowered Q can't answer.","Your tank-item spike and W-poke roughly match his bleed-stacking duel — itemization is starting to flip the lane your way.","Masterwork upgrades at 13 plus health items make you nearly unkillable while his single-target R execute can no longer burst you."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"drmundo","win":["Ornn","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Dr. Mundo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath gives unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield that out-trades his early Q cleaver chunks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R's long-range double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar lets you chain CC and Brittle burst through his Q-toss range — your cleanest kill window before he tanks up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire with boots makes you a durable W-poke bully, but his first health item also turns his Q heals on — trades get spongey on both sides."},{"when":"Late","text":"His R Maximum Dosage heal makes him nearly unkillable 1v1; you can't out-DPS the drain, so your value shifts entirely to teamfight CC and Masterwork upgrades."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit Level 3 to start trading with W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield before his Q stacks heals","Land E into your Q pillar for the knock-up and Brittle detonation at 6 to convert R into a kill","Win short trades and roam/teamfight on R before his drain-tank R heal makes him unkillable"],"foe":["Toss Q cleaver max-HP poke from range and heal off the passive without stepping into your W-E range","Stack health and survive to his R Maximum Dosage heal where he out-sustains everything","Drag the game long and even so his infinite scaling beats your single-target CC anchor"]},"early":"Mundo is dead weak levels 1-2 but so are you — no shield, no combo, mana-starved — so just farm and don't throw a Q he can ignore while he heals off his cleaver poke. The lane flips at Level 3: your W Bellows Breath is unstoppable, chunks his max HP, and shields his Q toss, so you out-trade his percent-HP poke once you can answer it. Don't chase him down — he'll just walk and heal — punish only when his Q is on cooldown.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are a coinflip of skill: you can land E into a Q pillar for a knock-up and Brittle, but he can Q-slow your dash and kite the followup, so set the pillar before you commit. Level 6 is your window — R's double knock-up plus E-Q stun chains enough CC that even his healing can't outrun the Brittle burst, and it's your last clean kill before his health items come online. Force the all-in here; once he hits his first item the lane goes even again.","late":"This is where you lose the 1v1 — his R Maximum Dosage is a massive heal that turns him unkillable, and you simply cannot out-damage the drain single-target. Stop trying to solo him; your win condition is the teamfight, where your E-Q knock-up, R double knock-up, and free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team an edge he can't match alone. Let him splitpush into your CC, never duel him at full HP, and play for objectives and 5v5s instead of the sidelane.","whys":["Mundo is one of the weakest level-1s, but you out-tempo him here since his Q cleaver only pokes and you can deny last-hits while he's mana-light.","Neither of you has a combo yet — he tosses Q to heal, you just farm; it's a skill-matched standoff with no kill pressure.","Your W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield answer his Q poke, but he can walk-and-heal, so the trade math is even.","You can E-into-Q-pillar for a knock-up, but he Q-slows your dash and kites the Brittle followup — it comes down to who lands their skillshot.","R's long-range double knock-up plus E-Q stun chains enough Brittle burst to beat his pre-item healing — your cleanest kill window.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire W-poke spike is real, but his first health item turns his Q heals on, so trades go spongey and even.","His R Maximum Dosage heal makes him unkillable 1v1 and he out-itemizes your single-target CC — the drain-tank reclaims the duel late."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"fiora","win":["Fiora","Fiora","Skill","Skill","Fiora","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You have no shield and no combo yet, so Fiora Q-dashes in for percent-HP true-damage vital procs while you eat poke and just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP poke plus a shield she cannot parry off you, so you finally trade back into her vitals."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up looks scary but a good Fiora W-parries the redirect or Q-dashes the line, so the all-in stays even-to-her here."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Her passive true damage ignores your armor stacking, but your free Masterwork upgrades and self-comboed CC finally out-value her single duel in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield, then trade every time her Q is on cooldown","Land E into your own Q-pillar for the knock-up so Brittle detonates before she can W-parry it","Survive lane even and convert to teamfights where your Masterwork upgrades and R double knock-up beat her single-target duel"],"foe":["Bait your W or E cast and W-parry it for the stun, then Q-dash in for free vital procs","Hit her passive vitals for percent-max-HP true damage that ignores all your armor and health stacking","Snowball the shieldless early levels, then split push you out with her dueling lead"]},"early":"Levels 1 and 2 are hers, full stop — you have no shield, no combo, and no mana, so don't contest her vitals. She Q-dashes in, procs a passive vital for percent-HP true damage, and dashes out before you can land anything. Just farm with the tip of your Q and accept the poke. The lane only turns at 3 when W (Bellows Breath) gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield she can't parry off you.","mid":"Once you have W and a second combo point this is genuinely even — your W shreds her health bar with percent-HP and the shield blunts her vital burst, but never throw a naked E she can W-parry into a stun. The trick is E into your own Q-pillar so the knock-up and Brittle land as one instant beat, not a telegraphed dash she can dodge or parry. At 6 your R double knock-up reads as a power spike, but a sharp Fiora parries the redirect or Q-dashes the line, so respect that the all-in can flip — only commit R when her W is down.","late":"Your armor and health mean nothing to her passive vitals — that's flat true damage and it ignores your whole tank build, so don't expect to win the straight 1v1 with items. What you DO win is the game around it: your level-13 Masterwork upgrades give your whole team an effective gold lead, and your R into E-Q-pillar self-combo chains CC no Fiora can parry her way out of in a 5v5. Don't try to splitpush her — group, force teamfights, and let your self-comboed knock-ups and Brittle decide it.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo, and no mana — she Q-dashes in for a percent-HP true-damage vital and you can only farm.","Still shieldless and comboless, you eat her vital procs while she dances out of any Q you throw.","W (Bellows Breath) gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and an unparryable shield, so you finally trade back evenly into her vitals.","With a second combo point you E into your own Q-pillar to knock her up, but she can Q-dash or W-parry the telegraph, so it stays a coin-flip of mechanics.","Your R double knock-up should win the all-in, but a good Fiora W-parries the redirect or dashes the line, tipping the 6 window back to her.","Your W-poke and shield hold the lane even on her, but her passive true damage keeps the straight duel a skill check neither side stomps.","Her true-damage vitals beat your armor in a 1v1, but your Masterwork upgrades and self-comboed R knock-up out-value her single-target dueling in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"galio","win":["Ornn","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Galio","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second point in your combo lets you E into your own Q pillar for a knock-up that detonates Brittle — punish any step-up Galio takes to last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Galio's ult window: his global R into a roaming threat plus his W taunt-while-tanky is his one stage to flip a trade or follow a gank — respect his all-in here."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots turns you into a W-percent-HP bully his MR stacking can't out-sustain in a straight trade."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team an effective gold lead — close before Galio's global utility decides fights elsewhere."}],"wants":{"you":["Land W (Bellows Breath) percent-max-HP poke that his MR stacking does nothing against, since it ignores resistances","Catch his step-ups with E into your Q magma pillar for a Brittle-detonating knock-up","Hit Level 6 and use R's double knock-up to win the all-in and enable ganks"],"foe":["Poke you with Q (Winds of War) and his magic-damage passive auto while you are mana-starved early","Bait your E-Q telegraph and absorb it with W's damage-reduction taunt","Stay even and use his global R to influence the map rather than duel you"]},"early":"Galio wants to chip you with Q tornadoes and his passive magic-damage autos while you are mana-hungry and comboless at Levels 1-2 — just farm and don't burn mana trying to trade back yet. Your W (Bellows Breath) is the key: it deals percent-max-HP damage and ignores his stacked MR entirely, so once you have it at 3 you can shrug his poke and answer with damage his anti-AP build can't reduce. Don't throw a raw E at him — he'll just eat it with his W taunt's damage reduction. Wait until your Q pillar is down so the E into terrain knocks him up.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are your real edge: with a second combo point you E into your own Q magma pillar, knock him up, and detonate Brittle with a W auto — a chunk his MR can't soften because the percent-HP and Brittle ignore resists. Bait his W taunt before you commit; once it's on cooldown his short-range body is yours. Level 6 is his one window — his global R and tanky taunt let him flip a trade or follow a gank — so play that level honestly and don't overstay if his jungler is unknown.","late":"Once you hit your first tank item you out-bully him in a straight lane, and at 13 your free Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead he can't match as a single utility tank. You stay favoured because your percent-HP W and self-comboed CC don't care about his MR stacking. The risk isn't the duel — it's his global R deciding a fight on the other side of the map, so push your lead into objectives and end before his roam-utility outscales your reach.","whys":["You concede most level 1s, but Galio is a slow, short-range AP tank with no early all-in — last-hit freely while his Q poke barely dents you.","Neither of you has a real combo yet; he pokes with Q and his magic auto, you just farm and hold mana, so the lane sits even.","You get W's percent-HP poke that ignores his stacked MR, but he can taunt-tank your raw E with damage reduction — a genuine coin-flip stage.","Your second combo point lets you E into your Q pillar for a Brittle knock-up he can't out-sustain, and his MR does nothing against percent-HP damage.","Galio's R goes global and his W taunt makes him tankiest here — this is his one window to flip a trade or follow a gank, so it's his.","Your first tank item plus W turns you into a percent-HP bully his anti-AP build can't reduce — force trades on his Q cooldown.","Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your team an effective gold lead his single-target utility can't match — close while you out-itemize him."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"gangplank","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Gangplank","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"With Q and W online your Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and shield finally let you trade through his barrel chains instead of just eating them."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R gives a long-range double knock-up that flips any all-in and lets you Brittle-burst a Gangplank caught without W up — your cleanest kill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Sunfire/Heartsteel spike makes you a durable W-poke bully, but watch his Sheen-Trinity barrel rhythm overtaking your trade math."},{"when":"Late","text":"Gangplank's stacked barrels, crit, and global R out-scale your single-target presence — his 2+ item window beats your duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 so Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and its shield let you trade back through barrel poke","Land E into your Q magma pillar for a knock-up, then Brittle-auto him before his W frees the CC","Snowball your level 6 R all-in and end the game before his barrel-crit-global scaling takes over"],"foe":["Chain barrels at max range and detonate them to poke you without entering your W or E reach","Use W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse your E-Q stun and slow, then heal the trade back","Stack passive crit and barrels and scale into a global-R, splitpush threat you cannot duel"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are rough for you — you have no shield, no combo, and you are mana-starved, so just last-hit and accept barrel poke rather than walking up into a chain you can't answer. Don't waste E chasing a single barrel; he'll just place another. Everything changes at 3: once Bellows Breath is up its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you walk through a barrel detonation and trade back, and his W can't out-sustain that if you punish his cooldowns.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are a knife-fight: you can punish an overextended Gangplank with E into your Q pillar for the knock-up, but his W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses that stun and the slow, so bait it out before you commit. At 6 your R is the swing — the long-range double knock-up lets you close his kite gap and Brittle-burst him, and that's your best kill window before his items. Hold E for when his W is down, not when it's up.","late":"This is where he reclaims it. A barrel-stacked, crit-itemized Gangplank pokes you out before you reach W range, his global R lets him impact every map fight, and his percent-scaling damage chews your armor. Your free Masterwork upgrades keep your team strong, but the straight 1v1 tips to him at 2+ items. Win the lane early on your 3-and-6 windows so his scaling never gets to matter, and group rather than try to splitpush-duel him.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and bad mana — but his early is just barrels, so farm safely and don't trade what you can't answer yet.","Still pre-W, his max-range barrel chain pokes you for free; soak it, hold E, and wait for level 3.","Bellows Breath comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you walk through a barrel and trade back harder than his W can heal.","Even fight: your E-Q pillar knock-up punishes him, but his W cleanses the stun and slow, so it's a bait-and-cooldown game.","Skill window — your R double knock-up wins the all-in, but a well-saved W still cleanses your engage, so it's about who plays the cooldown right.","His Sheen-barrel spike and crit start overtaking your tank-item trade math; he pokes you out before you reach W range.","Stacked barrels, crit and global R out-scale your single-target presence — he kites and pokes you down in the even-gold late game."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"gnar","win":["Gnar","Gnar","Skill","Ornn","Gnar","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Gnar boomerangs (Q) and hops you for free while you have no shield, no combo, and no mana — eat it and farm."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Second point in your E-into-Q-pillar lets you punish a Gnar who steps up to last-hit in melee range with a knock-up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Mega Gnar's GNAR! transform + boomerang AOE stun (R) is his all-in window — his stun outranges and pre-empts your E-Q setup."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike plus W's percent-HP unstoppable poke turns you into a lane bully Gnar can no longer kite for free."}],"wants":{"you":["Wall a kiting Gnar with your Q pillar, then E into it for the knock-up and Brittle detonation","Catch him in mini form when his Rage bar is low so he can't transform out of your R","Hit your first-item spike and W-poke his percent-HP down once he can't hop away safely"],"foe":["Kite you in mini form with boomerang (Q) and hops while your shield and combo are down","Save Mega transform for your E-Q commit so his AOE stun (R) interrupts your all-in","Stack Rage and time GNAR! to all-in you the moment your W shield is on cooldown"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are miserable here and you just accept it — you have no shield, no combo, and barely any mana, while mini-Gnar boomerangs (Q) you and hops in and out of poke range for free. Don't chase his hops, don't waste E trying to gap-close onto a slippery target; just last-hit and soak. At 3 you finally get Q and W together, and W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus its shield let you trade back into his pokes instead of only eating them — that's where this stops being one-sided.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are your first real edge: a second point in the combo means if Gnar walks up to CS in mini form, you can Q a pillar behind him and E into it for the knock-up, then Brittle-amp the follow-up. The trap at 6 is his transform — Mega Gnar's boomerang AOE stun (R) outranges your telegraphed E-Q and can interrupt your all-in, so do NOT commit into a full Rage bar. Bait the transform or fight him while he's still mini, and use your own R double knock-up only when his stun is already spent.","late":"Once you hit your first tank/health item your W-poke and durability flip the lane — Gnar can no longer kite you down for free, and your Q-wall punishes every hop he makes near you. From there you out-scale him as a teamfight anchor: your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 hand your whole team a gold lead, and your chained CC into Brittle burst dwarfs a single Mega-Gnar stun in a 5v5. Close space, wall his escape routes, and let your durability make his poke irrelevant.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo, and no mana at level 1 — Gnar just boomerangs and hops you, so farm and concede it.","Still no W shield to answer his poke; mini-Gnar kites your melee range with Q and free hops at level 2.","Q and W come online and W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale lets you trade back — the lane evens out into a skill fight.","Your second combo point means E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups punish any Gnar who steps up to last-hit in melee.","Mega Gnar's AOE stun (R) outranges and pre-empts your telegraphed E-Q, so he owns the all-in at 6 with full Rage.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike plus W-poke makes you a lane bully Gnar can no longer kite for free.","Free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your chained Brittle CC out-value a single Mega stun — you anchor the fights he can't win."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"gragas","win":["Ornn","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Gragas","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"With Q and W up you slam a magma pillar and W-poke percent-HP through his sustain — your first real trade window."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"E into your own Q pillar knocks him up and applies Brittle, turning a clean combo into a chunk he can't pool away."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His threat window: Gragas E-flash or E into R can knock you into tower or set up a gank before your own R lands."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots makes you a durable W-poke bully — tank his body-slam and out-trade his AP brawl."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 3 and W-poke his max-HP through his Q-pool sustain","Land E into your Q pillar for the Brittle knock-up he can't body-slam out of","Itemize health/armor and become the durable lane anchor he can't burst"],"foe":["Body-slam E in, R you toward tower or his jungler, then W to tank the trade back","Sustain every poke with his Q pool and out-brawl you in extended AP fights","Use E displacement to dodge your telegraphed E-Q knock-up setup"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you just farm — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so don't contest his Q-pool sustain trades yet. At 3 it flips: W gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, so you can finally trade back through his Q heal. Watch his E body-slam — that's his only engage and his only escape, so don't get caught walking up when it's off cooldown.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are your edge: a second point in your combo lets you E into a Q magma pillar for a knock-up plus Brittle, and his W damage reduction doesn't stop the displacement. The danger is 6 — his E into R can fling you into tower or toward a ganking jungler before your own R is online, so hold respect for that window. Once your R is up, your double knock-up plus Brittle out-CCs his single E displacement in any all-in.","late":"Your first item turns you into a near-unkillable W-poke bully — Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots lets you tank his body-slam and chunk his max HP while he can't burst through your armor and shield. Unlike most scaling matchups you don't fall off here: he's an AP bruiser, not a hard carry, so your Masterwork upgrades at 13 keep your team's gold lead growing while you anchor fights. Keep landing E-Q into his pool cooldown and he never gets the extended brawl he wants.","whys":["You're one of the weakest level-1s — no shield, no combo, mana-hungry — so just farm and let his Q-pool poke whiff on minions.","Even stage: he has Q sustain but no real burst yet, and you still lack your W shield to trade — neither of you wins this level.","Q and W come online: your unstoppable W poke chunks his max HP and the shield blunts his body-slam trade-back.","E into your Q pillar knocks him up with Brittle — his W damage reduction and Q heal can't answer the displacement combo.","His spike: E-flash or E into R can fling you into tower or a gank before your R is up to answer his displacement.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a durable W-poke bully — you tank his slam and out-trade his AP brawl.","He's a bruiser, not a hard carry, so you don't fall off — Brittle-amped CC and Masterwork upgrades keep you ahead at 2+ items."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"garen","win":["Garen","Garen","Garen","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Garen Q silences your cast and empowers a strike while you have no shield, no combo, and a thin manabar — he owns the level-1 walk-up."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once W (Bellows Breath) and Q are up you stabilize — W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield finally let you trade back into his short Q-strike."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) gives a long-range double knock-up that triggers Brittle — your hardest all-in and your clean window before his execute scales."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"You become the teamfight anchor with free Masterwork upgrades at 13 while Garen's R true-damage execute stays single-target — your value spreads, his doesn't."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive Levels 1-2 farming under tower and reach W (Bellows Breath) so the silence stops free-trading you","Land E into a Q-pillar knock-up to set Brittle, then detonate with W for a percent-HP burst he can't W-mitigate","Hit Level 6 and your first tank item, then anchor teamfights where his single-target R execute is wasted"],"foe":["Walk up level 1-2 and land Q to silence your cast plus the empowered strike before you have a shield","Use W (Courage) to cut your W exhale and E-Q burst, then disengage with passive regen out of vision","Stack HP and itemize his R true-damage execute to delete you in extended even-gold sidelanes"]},"early":"Levels 1 and 2 are miserable for me here — I have no shield, no combo, and a thin manabar, and Garen's Q both silences my cast and lands an empowered strike, so I lose every walk-up. Don't contest the early CS war; sit back and last-hit with the tip of Q. The moment I hit 3 and have W (Bellows Breath) up, the lane changes: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield finally let me eat his short Q-trade and live, and his Q silence can't stop W because it makes me unstoppable mid-cast.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even out — I get a second combo point and can punish his step-up by E-dashing into a Q-pillar for a knock-up, then exhaling W to set Brittle and burst him. The catch is his W (Courage) cuts my E-Q burst and gives him tenacity, so bait it out before I commit. Level 6 is my window: R's double knock-up is unstoppable to set up, triggers Brittle, and beats his all-in — and his passive only regens when he's left lane, so pin him and he can't reset.","late":"My team value runs away from him here — at 13 my free Masterwork upgrades give the whole team an effective gold lead, and in a teamfight his R is one execute on one target while my E-Q and R chain CC across the fight. The danger is the isolated sidelane: a fed Garen stacks HP, his R missing-HP true damage ignores my armor stacking, and he can short-trade then vanish on his passive regen. Don't duel him alone late — group, let my upgrades and CC anchor the fight, and make his single-target kit irrelevant.","whys":["I have no shield, no combo, and barely any mana at level 1 — his Q silences my cast and empowers a strike, so I just concede the walk-up and farm.","Still no W to answer him, and his Q silence shuts my only ranged poke — he free-trades while I last-hit with Q tip.","His Q-strike and W tenacity still let him short-trade me before my E-Q combo is fully online; I trade back but he edges level 3.","Once W (Bellows Breath) blunts his trade and my E-into-Q-pillar knock-up threatens him, the lane goes even — bait his W (Courage) before committing.","R (Call of the Forge God) is a long-range double knock-up that triggers Brittle and beats his all-in — and his passive can't regen while I keep him pinned in lane.","My first tank item lets me W-poke and tank his short trades, but his W damage-cut and HP keep it close — skill decides the all-in.","Free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make me a teamfight anchor while his R is a single-target execute — my value spreads across the fight, his doesn't."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"graves","win":["Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Graves","Graves","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"With Q-pillar plus W you can E into your own Q to knock Graves up and W-Brittle him before his E dash resets."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second combo point lets you E-Q stun him out of his True Grit kiting pocket and punish a missed E."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Graves' biggest swing: his Collateral Damage burst plus E double-dash and Smoke Screen blind let him chunk and reset before your R lands."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Once you have Heartsteel/Sunfire and Masterwork upgrades at 13, his ADC-tanky build can't kite your percent-HP W or survive a clean R."}],"wants":{"you":["Wall him against a Q-pillar with E so the knock-up Brittle-detonates before he E-dashes out","Bait his Smoke Screen, then W-poke through it since unstoppable percent-HP damage doesn't care about the blind","Hit your tank first-item spike and force a side-lane all-in before his shotgun crit build comes online"],"foe":["Kite your telegraphed E-Q with his double E dash and burst you on True Grit","Drop Smoke Screen on himself to blind your auto-Brittle procs and walk away","Stack tanky-ADC items and reach 2-item Collateral Damage burst to outrange your combo"]},"early":"Graves is melee-range for a ranged champ, so this isn't the kite-from-1200 nightmare other ADCs are — but his shotgun autos and Buckshot still chunk you at levels 1-2 when you have no shield and no combo. Don't walk up to last-hit into a fresh Buckshot; tank a little and farm with Q from range. The second you hit 3 you have W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus the Q-pillar, and that's your first real bite: he has to respect that you can E into your own wall and knock him up.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where you take over the lane. Your E-into-Q-pillar stun is the answer to his kiting — if he uses his E dash to reposition for a Buckshot, that's your window to dash in, wall him, and W-Brittle him while he's knocked up and his dash is down. Bait the Smoke Screen first; the blind shuts off his autos too, and your W damage is percent-HP and doesn't miss. The one stage to respect is 6: his Collateral Damage plus double-dash burst can chunk you before your R charges, so don't face-tank a fully loaded combo.","late":"You win the long game here. Graves builds tanky for an ADC but it's still ADC HP, and your W carves percent-max-HP through it while your E-Q and R lock him for the Brittle detonations he can't dash out of. At 13 your free Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead, and a clean R double knock-up deletes his kiting space. Don't let him farm jungle camps uncontested into a Collateral Damage one-shot build — close it before he gets there.","whys":["You have no shield or combo at 1 and his shotgun autos hurt, but he's melee-range and can't run you down either — last-hit at Q range and take the farm.","Your level-2 Q-pillar plus a point in W lets you threaten an E-wall knock-up before he has his E dash up to escape it.","At 3 your full E-into-Q-pillar combo plus W's percent-HP Brittle exhale out-trades his Buckshot and punishes any step-up.","Your second combo point means a missed Graves E gets him stunned against your pillar and W-Brittled before True Grit can heal it.","Graves owns 6: Collateral Damage burst, his double E dash, and a self-Smoke-Screen blind let him chunk and reset before your R lands.","His shotgun crit items spike harder than your tank first item in the raw duel — his Smoke Screen blinds your auto-Brittle procs while he kites.","Your W shreds his ADC-tanky HP with percent damage, your R locks him for Brittle, and Masterwork upgrades at 13 swing the whole game."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"gwen","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Gwen","Gwen","Gwen"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You both farm, but you can shove her off the wave with Q line damage before she snowballs to her item spike."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield trade evenly into her Q true-damage poke and E lifesteal."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Needlework gives ranged true-damage poke and a chase tool that outranges your telegraphed E-Q knock-up."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Once she has Riftmaker/Nashor's her W mist makes her untargetable to your E and R while she shreds your armor with true damage."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into a Q-pillar knock-up while she is outside her W mist circle","Use W's percent-HP exhale and shield to win short trades before her E attack-speed ramps","Shove waves with Q and roam/help your team end before her Riftmaker scaling lands"],"foe":["Drop W Hallowed Mist to go untargetable and dodge your E-Q and R entirely","Stack Q true-damage marks and snip with R Needlework to whittle your armor stacking","Survive to Riftmaker/Nashor's and out-duel you with sustained true damage at 2+ items"]},"early":"You start ahead, so use it: at 1-2 your Q line damage shoves Gwen off the wave and denies farm before her scaling gets rolling — she has no E sustain yet and no clean answer to your poke. From 3 it settles into a reads game: Bellows Breath is unstoppable, deals percent-max-HP damage, and shields you, so it trades evenly into her Q true damage and E attack-speed — but don't force the E-into-Q-pillar knock-up blindly, because Hallowed Mist makes her untargetable and erases the combo. Land it when she steps outside the mist or wastes W, then reset.","mid":"Level 6 tilts her way — Needlework gives her ranged true-damage poke and chase that outrange your telegraphed E-Q, and her first AP item snips through your armor stacking faster than your tank spike can answer. Stop hunting even trades and start playing map: shove with Q, use the tempo to roam, and set up cross-lane plays with Call of the Forge God. In lane, only commit when her W mist is down — a clean E-Q knock-up into your R through the wave is still a kill window with jungle help, but a whiffed combo into mist is pure loss.","late":"Riftmaker and Nashor's make her a duelist you should never touch alone — her sustained true damage ignores your resists and her mist dodges your E, Q, and R, so the side-lane 1v1 is hers. Your job is the teamfight: land a cross-map Call of the Forge God, chain the E-Q knock-up onto whoever the ram flattens, and let your team melt her while she's forced to hold W for your CC. Between fights you print value with Masterwork upgrades she can't match. Be the engine of the 5v5 and close before her item scaling decides everything.","whys":["You are both among the weakest level-1s, but your Q line damage lets you shove her off the wave and deny early farm.","Neither of you has a real level-2 spike, and your Q poke keeps her honest while she has no E sustain yet.","Your W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield trade evenly with her Q true damage and E attack-speed — genuinely skill-based.","Your E-Q knock-up punishes a mistimed step-up, but her W mist can erase the combo, so it comes down to who reads who.","Her R Needlework adds ranged true-damage poke and chase that outrange your telegraphed E-Q, edging the 6 window to her.","Her first AP item lets her snip your armor with true damage faster than your tank spike can answer in lane.","Riftmaker and Nashor's let her out-duel you outright — her true damage ignores your stacking and her W mist dodges your CC, so let your team handle her."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Skill","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Ornn","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-3","text":"Heimer plants his turret grid and walls you off the minions with W rockets — his hardest zoning window before your combo exists."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar lets you stun him through his turret line and W-Brittle burst him — your cleanest kill window all lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel or Sunfire plus boots lets you walk the W poke and turret tickle, tanking the grid to all-in on his E-grenade cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 turn teamfights, but a fed splitpushing Heimer with full turret zones can punish a 1v1 — group and let your CC chain win the 5v5."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit Level 6 and chain E-into-Q-pillar knock-up into R so he cannot kite, then W-Brittle for percent-HP burst","Buy a tank-health first item (Heartsteel/Sunfire) so you tank the turret grid and W rockets and all-in through them","Group for teamfights where your free Masterwork upgrades and double knock-up beat his immobile turret setup"],"foe":["Wall you off the wave with turrets and W rockets so you bleed CS and HP without ever reaching W range","Land his E stun grenade to peel your E-Q engage and reset his zone before your combo lands","Stay back behind the turret line, scale, and splitpush with a full grid so you can never 1v1 him"]},"early":"Heimer's whole early game is the turret grid plus W rockets — he walls you off the minions and chips you while you have no shield and no combo, so Levels 1-3 are miserable. Do not flail your E into the grid trying to engage; you'll eat turret fire and his E stun grenade and accomplish nothing. Soak XP at max range, last-hit what you can with Q's line damage from outside rocket range, and just survive to 3 when W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield finally let you trade back.","mid":"Levels 4-5 still belong to him — he can reposition turrets and keep the wall up faster than your single combo point can break it, and his E grenade peels your E. Bide your time. At 6 everything flips: R is a long-range double knock-up he can't kite with his stationary kit, and once you E-collide into a Q-pillar for the stun, he's locked in your W-Brittle burst range with no dash out. Bait his E grenade, then commit the full E-Q-R chain on his cooldown — that's your kill.","late":"Your first tank-health item (Heartsteel or Sunfire) lets you simply walk the turret grid and W poke and all-in on his E timer, so keep forcing it. The danger is the even-gold 1v1: a fed Heimer with a full grid up can splitpush and zone you off a side lane forever. Don't try to solo-clear his turrets — group. Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your double knock-up turn the 5v5, where his immobile turret setup can't out-zone a coordinated engage onto him.","whys":["You're both weak level 1 — he has no grenade stun yet and you just farm, so neither owns it; soak XP outside rocket range.","His turret grid and W rockets wall you off the wave and you still have no shield or combo to answer — he zones freely.","With Q, W and his E grenade up he repositions the grid faster than your single combo point can break it — he keeps the wall.","His E stun grenade peels your E engage and one combo point can't crack a full grid, so he edges 4-5 while you wait for R.","R's long-range double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun locks down an immobile Heimer, and W-Brittle bursts him through the grid.","You're even — your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike lets you tank the grid but his turrets are still chunky, so trade the all-in on his E cooldown.","Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and chained CC win the teamfight where his stationary turrets can't out-zone your engage."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"illaoi","win":["Ornn","Skill","Illaoi","Illaoi","Skill","Illaoi","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Before her tentacles spawn, your W exhale chunks her percent-HP and shields the return poke — the one window you out-trade her cleanly."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Her E rips your spirit and her field of tentacles slaps you for the duration — never trade standing on top of three tentacles."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up plus a W shield lets you survive her ult-fueled all-in and reset the lane to even."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her Mythic and tentacle stacks turn any extended fight into a sustain win for her — only commit when you can E-pillar her off the field."}],"wants":{"you":["Land the W exhale for percent-HP poke and the shield, then back off before her tentacles reload","Use E into a Q magma pillar to knock her UP and out of her own tentacle field","Hit Level 6 even and use R's double knock-up to blunt her ult all-in"],"foe":["Land E to rip your spirit so her tentacle field shreds your max HP while you reposition","Stack tentacles around you so every trade is amplified AOE you cannot escape","Drag the fight long with her sustain and Mythic so her field out-grinds your W shield"]},"early":"Level 1 is genuinely yours here — before her tentacles are up, your W exhale deals percent-HP and shields you, so step up and out-trade her clean. Once she has tentacles down by Level 3, the lane flips: do NOT stand in her field, because her E rips your spirit and every tentacle slaps you for the whole trade. Farm with Q's line, respect the tentacle count, and never walk in to last-hit on top of three of them.","mid":"Levels 4-5 belong to her if you trade naively — her tentacle field plus E sustain out-grinds your W pokes whenever you stand in it. Your job is to bait, not brawl: use E into your own Q magma pillar to knock her UP and drag the fight OFF her tentacles, where she is immobile and weak. At 6 you stabilize back to even — R's double knock-up and a fresh W shield let you survive her ult-amplified all-in and reset.","late":"Her first item is her best window — Mythic plus stacked tentacles turn any drawn-out fight into a sustain win, so don't sit in her field hoping your shield holds. At 2+ items it levels out: you become the near-unkillable anchor with Masterwork upgrades at 13, and teamfights are where your E-Q-R chain-CC and free item lead matter more than her single tentacle field. Don't 1v1 her on a Vault stack — make her fight you where there's only one tentacle, not five.","whys":["Before her tentacles spawn your W exhale poke and shield out-trade her at Level 1 cleanly.","Level 2 is a wash — she has one tentacle and you have W but no combo, so neither side commits.","With her tentacle field and E spirit-rip online she out-sustains your W pokes if you stand in it.","Her second tentacle and E sustain mean extended trades in her field grind you down all-lane.","Your R double knock-up plus a W shield blunts her ult all-in and pulls the lane back to even.","Her Mythic and stacked tentacles turn first-item fights into a sustain win you can't W through.","At 2+ items you're a teamfight anchor with Masterwork upgrades while she stays a single-target field — it evens out."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"irelia","win":["Skill","Skill","Irelia","Skill","Irelia","Irelia","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You have no shield and no combo yet, so eat her early Q-resets on the wave and just farm with Q tip rather than trading."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Bellows Breath (W) comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield is your first real answer to her Q-stacking-passive trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her threat window: with ult plus a stacked passive she can all-in through your CC if your E-Q knock-up is on cooldown — respect a flash-Q reset onto you."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 and tank items make you the unkillable anchor while her single-target combo bounces off — the duel and the teamfight flip to you."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into a Q-pillar or wall for the knock-up stun so Brittle amplifies your W and you win the trade outright","Survive her level-1-2 lane bully phase and farm to your W shield at 3 and your first tank item","Reach 13 for free Masterwork upgrades and become the teamfight anchor her single-target kit can't kill"],"foe":["Use Q to dash through minions and reset off your CC, weaving E-stun in to chunk you before your W is up","Stack her passive on you in short trades and snowball an early lead before you itemize","Get going early so she out-scales into a duelist who shreds your armor with passive true-damage"]},"early":"Levels 1 and 2 are hers — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so don't contest the wave. She'll Q-dash in, stack her passive and E-stun you if you step up, so last-hit with the tip of Volcanic Rupture (Q) and concede the early push. The moment you hit 3 and have Bellows Breath (W), your footing changes: W is unstoppable, shields you, and burns percent max-HP, so she can't simply Q-reset on you for free anymore.","mid":"This is the skill phase. Your whole kit is self-comboed, so you don't need to land E on her directly — dash into your own Q pillar (or a wall) to knock her up, then W applies Brittle and your auto detonates the bonus damage. The danger is her dashes: a telegraphed E-Q whiffs if she Q-resets through a minion mid-cast, so bait her Q out before you commit. At 6 she edges it — her ult plus a fully stacked passive can all-in through you if your knock-up is down, so don't trade into your own combo cooldown.","late":"The game swings your way once you itemize. At 13 your Living Forge upgrades your and your team's legendaries into Masterwork versions — that's an effective gold lead her snowball can't match. Stacked armor and health turn her single-target combo into chip damage, and your E-Q-R chain CC plus Brittle makes you the teamfight anchor she simply cannot kill. She can still splitpush and shred you 1v1 if she's fed, so group, force fights around your knock-ups, and let your durability do the work.","whys":["You both want the wave, but with no shield and no combo you just last-hit with Q tip while she's free to fish for resets — call it even survival, not a trade.","Neither of you commits hard yet; she can Q-reset and E but lacks the burst to kill, and you simply farm to your W power spike.","She owns this window — her Q-stacking passive and E-stun out-trade you in the gap before Bellows Breath gives you a shield and unstoppable poke.","With a second combo point you can E into a Q-pillar knock-up and Brittle-amplify a trade, matching her short-trade pressure — genuinely even.","Her level 6 is the threat spike: ult plus a stacked passive all-ins through you if your E-Q knock-up is on cooldown.","Her first-item snowball as a duelist beats your pre-tank-item body — she shreds you before your armor and health come online.","At 13 your Masterwork upgrades and tank itemization make you near-unkillable while her single-target combo bounces off — the duel flips to you."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"jax","win":["Ornn","Skill","Jax","Jax","Skill","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once W (Bellows Breath) is up, its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back into Jax and shrug his Q-W burst."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Jax's Counter Strike (E) dodges your autos and stuns — this is his window to win short trades before your full combo and R come online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R's charging knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun chains hard CC that beats a Jax all-in even through his R defensive stats."},{"when":"First item","text":"Your tank/health spike (Heartsteel or Sunfire + boots) makes you a W-poking lane bully who out-durables his Counter Strike windows."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 W (Bellows Breath) to trade with unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield that eats his Q-W burst","Land E (Searing Charge) into your own Q pillar for the knock-up stun, then weave Brittle autos","Hit 6 and first item, then own every all-in with R double knock-up before he out-scales"],"foe":["Bait your E-Q telegraph and hold Counter Strike (E) to dodge your autos and stun you mid-combo","Win short Q-W gap-close trades at 4-5 before your CC chain comes online","Survive to 2-3 items where his R defensive stats and on-hit DPS reclaim the extended duel"]},"early":"Jax is even-ish into you early but you actually own level 1 because he's a weak, no-shield laner too and his Q-W only matters once he commits. Concede nothing at 1-2 — just farm with Q's line and don't throw E into a Jax holding Counter Strike, because his E dodges your autos and stuns you. At level 3 your W (Bellows Breath) flips it: unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield blunts his all-in and applies Brittle for your follow-up.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are Jax's window — a second point in Counter Strike means he can eat your auto-trade, stun you, and Q-W back before your combo is whole, so don't walk into a held E. Bait the dodge: throw a Q pillar, wait out his E, then E-into-the-pillar for the knock-up stun and Brittle autos. At 6 your R's charging double knock-up wins the all-in even through his R's defensive stats — that's your clean kill window before items.","late":"Your first-item tank spike (Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots) makes you a durable W-poke bully who out-lasts his Counter Strike trades, and the lolalytics edge stays with you. The danger is letting it go even into 2-3 items, where his R defensive stats and stacked on-hit DPS reclaim the pure 1v1 — so press your item lead now and don't gift him the splitpush scaling. In teamfights you're far ahead: free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your E-Q-R CC chain anchor the fight while he's stuck side-laning.","whys":["You're both weak at 1 with no shield, but his Q-W only spikes on commit — deny his last-hits and don't feed a held Counter Strike.","Genuinely even at 2 — he can Q-W in but you have W next level, so trade pillars and farm rather than risk his E stun.","Jax edges it as his Counter Strike (E) dodges your autos and stuns through your trade before your full combo lands.","His second Counter Strike point lets him win short Q-W trades, and a held E blanks your E-Q telegraph — his cleanest window.","Even at 6 — your R double knock-up and E-Q stun chain beats his all-in, but his R defensive stats let him survive to fight back.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a W-poke lane bully who out-durables his Counter Strike DPS windows.","You hold the item-lead duel and the teamfight ceiling — free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your CC chain anchor while he's stuck splitting."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"jayce","win":["Jayce","Jayce","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Jayce's cannon Q acceleration-gate poke chunks you while you're shieldless and mana-starved — eat it and farm, don't chase."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — your unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield finally let you trade back through his poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q pillar knock-up: if he hammer-stances to all-in or mispositions, your double CC chain plus Brittle deletes a squishy Jayce."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots: you out-sustain his poke and W-chunk him every time he steps up to last-hit."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the shieldless levels 1-2 and farm with Q's line until W (Bellows Breath) is up at 3","Bait his E knockback / hammer-stance step-up, then E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up stun and Brittle detonation","Land R's charging knock-up to lock him for the E-Q follow-up before his ranged poke whittles you out"],"foe":["Acceleration-gate cannon Q poke you under tower while you have no shield or sustain","Hold his E knockback to cancel your E-Q gap-close and reset to max range","Keep the lane long and even so his poke and burst combo deny you ever reaching W range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are miserable and you just accept it — you have no shield, no combo, and no mana, while Jayce's accelerated cannon Q (boosted through his W gate) pokes you off every minion. Don't walk up to last-hit into the gate; use the far end of your own Q line to farm and let the poke land on your HP bar, not your tempo. The instant you hit 3 and have W (Bellows Breath), the lane changes: its unstoppable percent-max-HP exhale and shield let you chunk him and blunt any step-up, so he can't keep free-poking you.","mid":"Now you're the bully. With W's shield eating his cannon poke and your E-into-Q-pillar combo online at 4-5, every time he steps up to last-hit or commits a hammer-stance trade you E into your own pillar for a knock-up stun, then W-exhale Brittle and auto for the bonus burst. Bait his E knockback first — if you E before it's down he just punts you out of your combo. At 6, R's long-range charging knock-up gives you a second layer of CC he can't dash out of, and a chained R-E-Q on a squishy Jayce who overstayed is a kill.","late":"You stay ahead here — your first tank item (Heartsteel or Sunfire plus boots) makes you durable enough that his poke can't burst you, and your W keeps chunking him whenever he comes to farm. Unlike pure scalers, Jayce doesn't out-itemize you; he falls off relative to your free Masterwork upgrades at 13. Keep forcing him off the wave with W-poke and threaten the E-Q pillar so he can never settle into comfortable poke range, and your team value snowballs from there.","whys":["You're shieldless, comboless and mana-starved at 1 while Jayce's accelerated cannon Q pokes you for free — just farm.","He gets a second poke rotation and the W-gated acceleration before you have any shield, so he owns the level-2 trade outright.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online and its unstoppable shield-and-percent-HP exhale lets you trade back — but his poke still answers, so it's genuinely even.","Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up plus Brittle finally punishes any hammer-stance step-up harder than his poke trades back.","R's long-range charging knock-up chains into E-Q for a double-CC all-in Jayce can't dash out of, and Brittle amplifies the burst.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots make you tanky enough to ignore his poke while W keeps chunking him every time he last-hits.","He doesn't out-itemize you the way a scaler does, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 widen the gap as your durability hard-counters his poke."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"karma","win":["Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Q-pillar + W online: walk a minion wave, slam Q for a wall, then W her for unstoppable percent-HP fire she cannot interrupt with RQ root."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up into Brittle is a guaranteed kill window if she has no Flash and her E shield is down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a permanent lane bully who eats her Q poke and W-shoves her under tower."},{"when":"Karma early","text":"Her biggest window is Levels 1-2: she pokes your low base HP with Q before you have a shield, so just farm and do not walk into RQ range."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 3 for Q-pillar plus W so you have an unstoppable, root-immune percent-HP poke","Use E into your own Q-wall to knock her up and detonate Brittle when she steps up to poke","Hit your first health item and W-shove her under tower to deny CS and set up dives"],"foe":["Poke your low early HP with Q before you have W's shield online","Land RQ root plus tether to kite you out of W and E range","Shield allies with E and stay max range so your telegraphed E-Q never connects"]},"early":"Karma's Q poke stings at Levels 1-2 because you have no shield yet and your base HP is low, so just last-hit and refuse to chase her into RQ-root range. The moment you hit 3 the lane shifts: W makes you unstoppable while it exhales percent-HP fire and applies Brittle, and her RQ root cannot cancel it. Slam Q for a magma pillar so your E has a wall to knock her into, and start punishing every time she steps up to poke.","mid":"This is your phase. E into your own Q-pillar knocks her up, Brittle amplifies the follow-up, and W's shield blunts the only burst she has. At 6 your R is a long-range double knock-up that locks her down through her E move-speed buff — if she is out of Flash, R into Brittle deletes her. Force these all-ins on her E shield cooldown; her only out is range, so cut it off with your Q-wall.","late":"You stay ahead here too — your W percent-HP and CC chain ignore her squishy build, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 hand your whole team a gold lead her enchanting cannot match. Her one win condition is poking from max range in teamfights, so flank with E-Q knock-ups and don't let her safely shield a carry. Land R and she has no escape.","whys":["You have no shield and low HP at level 1, but she has no all-in either — just last-hit and respect her Q poke range.","Your W comes online and its unstoppable percent-HP fire and shield outpace her single Q's poke at level 2.","Q-pillar plus W lets you trade through her RQ root — she cannot interrupt your unstoppable W, so you win every exchange.","E into your own Q-wall knocks her up and detonates Brittle before her E shield can save her.","R is a long-range double knock-up into Brittle — on her Flash cooldown it is a guaranteed kill window she cannot escape.","Your first health item makes you tanky enough to ignore her Q poke and W-shove her off the wave under tower.","Your W percent-HP, CC chain, and free Masterwork upgrades at 13 out-value a squishy enchanter whose only out is max range."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"kassadin","win":["Skill","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Kassadin","Kassadin","Kassadin"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and shield let you trade into a Kassadin who has no escape until 6."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes any creep-shove overextension before his Riftwalk exists."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kassadin's Riftwalk (R) blink turns the lane upside down — he kites your telegraphed E-Q and stops dying to ganks."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Post-Rod-of-Ages Kassadin Riftwalks in, silences with Q and bursts you while his passive shield eats your W magic damage."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit your Lvl 3-4 power and shove him off CS while his Q silence is his only tool","Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up stun before he has Riftwalk to dodge it","Crash waves and roam/gank pre-6 to build a lead before his scaling outpaces you"],"foe":["Survive to 6 and use Riftwalk (R) to dodge your E-Q and dodge ganks","Farm safely behind his Q silence and magic shield until Rod of Ages / Tear come online","Stack Riftwalk charges and reach 2+ items where he kites and bursts you"]},"early":"Kassadin is melee-helpless at Levels 1-2 just like you are, so neither of you wins the opening — you both just farm. The lane turns at Level 3: once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, and he has no blink yet to answer it. Don't waste E chasing — he has nothing to punish you, so just shove and chip him with W. His only early tool is the Q silence, which he uses defensively to peel a trade, not to win one.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are your real window — your E into your own Q pillar knock-up lands clean because he still has no Riftwalk to dash out of it, so punish any time he steps up to last-hit. Crash the wave and look to roam, because everything inverts at 6: the moment he hits Riftwalk (R) he blinks over your telegraphed E-Q and stops dying to ganks. Get your lead in before that, because his Q silence also shuts off your W mid-combo.","late":"Once Kassadin has Rod of Ages and a couple items he owns this lane and the map — he Riftwalks in, silences you with Q to lock out your W shield, and bursts you while his passive magic shield blunts your only ranged damage. Your job was to make 6+ irrelevant; if you got ahead, hard-shove and group so his single-target threat means less, and let your team body him in a fight where your free Masterwork upgrades and CC chain still win. Do not try to 1v1 a fed Kassadin — he untargets and kites you to death.","whys":["Kassadin is melee-helpless at level 1 and so are you — nobody wins, you both farm for levels.","You get Q first and your magma pillar plus early W poke punish a Kassadin who has no Riftwalk and no answer.","Your level-3 Bellows Breath gives unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield he can't trade into, but his Q silence keeps it even.","You can land E into your Q pillar for a knock-up, but he can farm safely behind his Q silence and magic shield — it's a skill check.","Riftwalk (R) lets him blink over your telegraphed E-Q and dodge ganks, flipping the lane to him.","His Rod of Ages spike outraces yours — Riftwalk plus Q silence kites and locks out your combo.","Full-item Kassadin Riftwalks in, silences your W, and bursts you while his passive shield eats your magic damage — play for teamfights, not the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"kayle","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Kayle","Kayle","Kayle","Kayle"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Bellows Breath comes online — unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield let you chunk a meleed, item-less Kayle every time she walks up to last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Call of the Forge God plus an E-into-Q-pillar knock-up is your hardest all-in window — chain Brittle and burst her before she ever finishes her core."},{"when":"Kayle Lvl 11","text":"Her ranged form on E means she kites your telegraphed E-Q from outside W range and starts whittling you for free — the lane flips here."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Full-itemized Kayle with R invulnerability waveclears, splitpushes, and out-DPSes anything you bring to the duel — your single-target CC stops mattering."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with W's percent-HP poke and crash waves to deny her XP and delay her level 11 ranged spike","Land E into your Q-pillar for the knock-up, then Brittle-amp the burst before she has items","Force every all-in at level 6 with R's double knock-up while she is still melee and defenseless"],"foe":["Survive your melee range to level 11 where E goes ranged and she can kite your E-Q","Farm safely behind minions and use R invulnerability to deny your all-in and gank setups","Reach 2+ items and take over the map with waveclear, splitpush, and untouchable DPS"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you both farm — you have no shield or combo and she is a meleed scaler, so neither of you commits. The moment you hit 3 and have Bellows Breath, you own the trade: it is unstoppable, deals percent max-HP, and shields you, so step up and chunk her every time she walks to last-hit. She cannot answer that poke while she is still melee, so make her pay for every CS.","mid":"This is your whole window to make the lane matter. Levels 4-5 you punish any step-up with E into your own Q magma pillar for a knock-up, then auto for Brittle damage. At 6, R's charging knock-up plus the E-Q reset gives you a full lockdown all-in — kill her or shove her under tower and freeze her off XP. Every plate and every level you deny now is a minute her ranged form is delayed.","late":"Once Kayle hits 11 and her E goes ranged she kites your telegraphed E-Q from outside W range and starts free poke — the duel is gone. At 2+ items with R invulnerability she waveclears, splitpushes, and out-DPSes everything you have, and your single-target CC does nothing to a carry that just presses R through it. Don't 1v1 her late; group, use your free Masterwork upgrades and CC to win fights around her, and make your team's gold lead the win condition.","whys":["Kayle is a weak meleed level-1, but so are you — no shield, no combo, mana-starved — so nobody commits and you both just farm.","Still no Bellows Breath shield to trade safely and she has no item yet, so the level stays even and you trade CS.","Your W comes online with unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, but a careful Kayle just farms behind minions — it is even on skill.","You out-trade a meleed, item-less Kayle: E into your Q-pillar knock-up plus Brittle autos wins any step-up — but she edges it by farming safe to scale.","Your R double knock-up and E-Q is your hardest all-in, yet Kayle owns the stage because she only has to survive it to take over.","Your tank first-item makes you a lane bully, but Kayle's ranged-form E spike lets her kite your E-Q out of W range and whittle you.","Fully itemized Kayle presses R invulnerability through your CC and out-DPSes you — her hard scaling reclaims the duel for good."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"kennen","win":["Skill","Kennen","Kennen","Ornn","Kennen","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath) its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you finally trade back through Kennen's Q/W poke instead of just eating it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kennen's R (Slicing Maelstrom) plus his energy-fueled poke is his scariest window — he can chunk you and stun-zone you without ever entering your E-Q range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots turns you into a durable lane bully who shrugs off his Q/W poke and W-pokes him off the wave."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"With your tank items and Brittle online you survive his full R combo and your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up finally lands the all-in he kited all lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit Level 3 for W (Bellows Breath) so its unstoppable shield and percent-HP exhale answer his poke","Use your Q magma pillar as terrain to guarantee an E (Searing Charge) knock-up when he steps up to last-hit","Stack health/tank items so his AP poke chips for nothing and you out-sustain the lane into teamfights"],"foe":["Kite at max range with Q (Thundering Shuriken) and Q/W poke, never stepping into your W or E range","Hold R (Slicing Maelstrom) plus his move speed to dodge your telegraphed E-Q and stun you from outside it","Whittle your HP with energy-free poke so he never runs out of resources and you can never all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a farm-and-eat-poke phase — you have no shield and no combo, so just last-hit with the tip of Q (Volcanic Rupture) and accept his Q (Thundering Shuriken) and auto poke without flinching. The lane swings at 3 when W (Bellows Breath) comes online: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and the shield let you finally trade back instead of being free poke fodder. Don't throw a raw E (Searing Charge) at him — without a Q pillar or wall behind him it won't knock up, and he just sidesteps with his move speed.","mid":"This is his strongest window and you have to respect it. At 6 his R (Slicing Maelstrom) plus stacked Q/W poke can chunk you and stun-zone you from outside your reach, and his energy means he never runs dry. Your job is to not die to poke and not waste E whiffing on a kiter — set up your Q magma pillar FIRST, then E into it so he eats a guaranteed knock-up, and only commit when his R is down. Levels 4-5 are your cleaner window before his 6: a second combo point lets you punish any greedy step-up.","late":"You take this over once you're itemized. Your first tank item (Heartsteel or Sunfire) plus boots makes his AP poke chip for almost nothing, and at 2+ items you survive his full R combo and W-poke him off every wave. With Brittle online your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and R double knock-up finally cash in the all-in he kited all lane, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make you the better teamfight anchor — don't chase him in the sidelane, drag him to fights where his squishy frame folds to your CC chain.","whys":["Neither of you does much at 1 — you have no shield or combo, he's just landing Q pokes, so farm even and don't trade.","His Q (Thundering Shuriken) and auto poke outrange everything you have before W, and his move speed keeps him out of your reach.","He out-pokes you with energy-free Q/W and kites your raw E (Searing Charge), which can't knock up without a pillar behind him.","Your W (Bellows Breath) and second combo point let you set a Q pillar and E-knock-up any greedy step-up before his 6.","His R (Slicing Maelstrom) plus poke wins this window — he stun-zones and chunks you from outside your E-Q range.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes his AP poke worthless and lets you W-poke and tank trades comfortably.","At 2+ items you eat his full combo and land E-into-Q-pillar plus R double knock-up, and your Masterwork upgrades win the fights."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"kled","win":["Skill","Kled","Kled","Kled","Skill","Kled","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Kled mounted Q-grab pulls you and starts a remount skirmish before you have W's shield — concede the level and last-hit safely."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus shield finally lets you tank a Skaarl all-in and Brittle him back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up answers his R Chaaaaaaaarge!!! engage — bait the dismount, then E-into-Q-pillar stun him as he tries to remount."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"A fed Kled hard-scales — his Q grab and bonus AD shred your armor in extended fights while you anchor for the team instead of dueling him."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield so his skirmishes stop free-winning","Land E into your own Q magma pillar to knock him up and Brittle-detonate during his dismount window","Survive his early all-ins, hit 6, and convert R double knock-up into ganks and a teamfight anchor"],"foe":["Use mounted Q grab to pull you and burst trades before you have W up","Bait your E-Q telegraph, dismount to dodge it, then remount and re-engage","Snowball the early skirmishes and out-scale into 2+ items where his AD shreds your armor"]},"early":"Kled owns the opening levels — his mounted Q grab yanks you in and his Skaarl skirmishing out-trades you before you have any tools, so just farm and eat a little poke at Levels 1-2 like you do into everyone. Don't throw a level-1 E hoping to wall-stun him; he'll dismount and dodge the telegraph, and you'll be stuck on cooldown. Your whole early plan is reaching Level 3: once W (Bellows Breath) is up you get unstoppable percent-HP exhale and a shield that finally lets you take a Q-grab trade and Brittle him back instead of just losing it.","mid":"Levels 4-5 still belong to Kled — his remount aggression and Courage of the Colossus shielding mean a straight skirmish favors him, so trade with W exhale and back off rather than committing E early. Level 6 is your equalizer: when he R-charges in to engage, bait the dismount, then E into your own Q magma pillar to knock him up and stun him as he tries to remount Skaarl, and your own R adds a second long-range double knock-up that wins the all-in. Don't blow E first — hold it for his dismount or you're just feeding a free remount.","late":"This is a real EVEN lane decided by who hit their power first, and late game tips back toward Kled as a hard scaler — his bonus AD and Q grab chunk through your armor stacking in any extended 1v1. Stop trying to solo him; your value is the team. Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole side an effective gold lead, and your E-Q-pillar plus R double knock-up are far scarier in a 5v5 than dueling a fed Skaarl. Anchor the fight, peel, and let his single-target threat get swallowed.","whys":["Both of you are weak level 1, but his mounted Q grab and Skaarl aggression edge a genuine coin-flip while you have no shield yet.","His Q grab and remount skirmishing out-trade you before W is up — concede and farm.","Even with W's shield online, Kled's Courage-of-the-Colossus all-in still wins the straight skirmish at this point.","His second-point dismount-remount damage out-paces your pre-6 combo; trade with W exhale and don't over-commit E.","R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun answers his R engage — bait the dismount and the all-in flips to a coin-flip you can take.","His first-item AD spike and Q grab reclaim the duel before your tank item makes you unkillable.","Late, your free Masterwork upgrades and E-Q-R teamfight CC outvalue a fed Kled's single-target shredding — anchor, don't duel."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"ksante","win":["Skill","Skill","K'Sante","K'Sante","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once W (Bellows Breath) is up, his percent-HP poke and shield let you trade back into K'Sante's Q pokes and blunt his dash-in."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"K'Sante's window: a second point in Q plus W (block + dash) lets him eat your E-Q knockup setup and answer your trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up wins the all-in before his R isolation flips the duel — your cleanest 6 spike."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"K'Sante reclaims the duel: ultimate R strips his resists into a fighter that ignores your armor stacking and isolates you."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 3 W (Bellows Breath) to poke his max-HP and shield through his Q chunks","Land E into a Q-pillar (Searing Charge into Volcanic Rupture) to knock him up and Brittle-burst before his W block is up","Hit your Level 6 R double knock-up to win the all-in before he scales into a fighter"],"foe":["Block your W and E with his W (Ntofo Strikes / dash block) and dash through your telegraphed E-Q","Poke you with Q knock-up procs while you are mana-starved early and shove the wave","Reach 2+ items and ult (R) to strip his resists, isolate you, and out-duel your tank shell"]},"early":"K'Sante's Q pokes and his W that blocks and dashes are the early problem — at Levels 1-2 you have no shield and no combo, so just farm and don't walk into his Q knock-up empowered third hit. The moment you hit Level 3 and have W (Bellows Breath), you stabilize: it makes you unstoppable, shields you, and chunks his max HP while applying Brittle, so you can finally trade back into his pokes instead of eating them. Mind your mana — W is expensive and you can't spam it.","mid":"This is K'Sante's clearest window. At Levels 4-5 his second Q point and his W block let him soak your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and answer the trade, so don't throw E-Q raw — bait his W block first. Level 6 swings back to you: your R is a long-range double knock-up that chains into Brittle, and it wins the all-in before his R isolation can flip you. Use your 6 to punish any greedy step-up while he's still squishy.","late":"Even gold, this duel belongs to K'Sante late. His R strips his own resists into a fighter with percent-HP and an isolation that drags you 1v1 — exactly the true/percent-HP profile that ignores your armor stacking and shell. Don't try to solo-duel him at 2+ items; lean on what you do best — your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make your whole team stronger, so play for teamfights where your E-Q-R CC chain and his isolated all-in cost him the angle. Never get caught alone in his R.","whys":["Both of you are weak at Level 1 — you have no shield or combo, but he only has a single Q poke, so it is an even farming stalemate.","He can start chaining Q knock-up procs, but with no W block point yet he can't punish hard — neither of you commits.","K'Sante owns this: his second Q and W block let him eat your E-Q setup and answer your trade-back before you fully spike.","With Q rank up and W (block + dash) he soaks your knock-up combo and out-trades your mana-starved shell.","Your R double knock-up wins the all-in here, but his R isolation means it is a knife-edge skill window, not a free kill.","Your first tank item (Heartsteel/Sunfire) lets you W-poke and tank trades, but his fighter items keep pace — it stays even.","He out-scales: R strips his resists into percent-HP isolation that ignores your armor, so play teamfights, not the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"lillia","win":["Skill","Lillia","Lillia","Lillia","Lillia","Lillia","Lillia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You have no shield and no combo yet, so her passive DOT and W bounce chip you for free while you can only farm — accept it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q-pillar knock-up is your one clean kill window, but if she has her own R up she can sleep you mid-combo and reset the fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"A Sunfire/Heartsteel + boots lets you tank her DOT poke and W-Brittle her when she dashes in, but she just E-bounces back out of your range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even-gold Lillia kites your whole team with W slows and R area-sleep — your value shifts entirely to the Masterwork upgrades you hand your carries at 13."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your own Q-pillar for the terrain knock-up, then W-Brittle and auto her while she's airborne","Use Q-pillar as a wall to cut off her W/E kite path and trap her against terrain","Survive the early DOT poke to farm and convert your free off-map item purchases into a teamfight lead"],"foe":["Kite you forever with W-bounce and E move speed, never standing in W-Brittle range","Land her R sleep to cancel your E-Q combo or peel for a gank","Poke you down with passive DOT and outscale into an even-gold late game where she anchors nothing but you can't catch her"]},"early":"Lillia just outranges your whole early game — you have no shield, no combo, and mana problems at Levels 1-2, so don't chase her W bounce into a missed E. Her passive DOT and W will chip you while you last-hit, and that's fine; you cannot punish her until Level 3 when Q and W come online. Don't throw E to engage early — whiffing it leaves you naked while her DOT ticks. Just farm with Q and eat the poke.","mid":"At 3-5 your W gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, so you can finally trade back when she dashes in — but she rarely commits, she just W-bounces and kites with E move speed out of your range. Your one real shot is the E-into-Q-pillar knock-up: wall her against terrain, knock her up, then W-Brittle and auto. At 6 your R double knock-up is the cleanest all-in you'll get, but respect her R — if her sleep is up she'll knock you out of your combo and reset.","late":"This stays even because neither of you really wins: she can't burst a tank with item upgrades, and you can't catch a champion built entirely to kite. Your Q-pillar is your only tool to body-block her W/E escape in skirmishes — use it to wall off her kite lane, not as a damage poke. Your true late value isn't this duel at all; it's the free Masterwork upgrades you hand your carries at 13, so play for teamfights and let your team answer her sleep-and-run.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and no mana — but Lillia is a squishy skirmisher who also can't kill yet, so it's a wash while you both farm.","Her passive DOT and W bounce chip you for free and you still have no W shield to trade back — she owns the level-2 poke window.","Even with Q and W up, she just W-bounces and kites with E move speed out of your Brittle range before you can punish.","Your E-Q-pillar knock-up is your only engage, but she dodges the telegraph with E and resets the trade with her bounce.","Your R double knock-up is real, but her R sleep cancels your combo mid-cast and lets her escape the all-in.","Your tank item lets you survive her DOT, but it doesn't help you catch her — she E-bounces out of your W range every trade.","In an even-gold game she kites you and your team forever with W slows and area-sleep, and you can't itemize your way to catching her."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"lucian","win":["Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Lucian's passive double-shot and Q poke chunk you while you have no shield, no combo and no mana — eat last-hits at range and do not contest."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) finally lets you shrug a trade — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield blunt his double-shot when he steps in to last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q pillar is your all-in: the charging elemental knock-up plus a terrain stun pins his E-dash and lets W-Brittle detonate before he kites out."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"With Heartsteel/Sunfire and Masterwork upgrades at 13 you become unkillable to his auto-DPS — walk him down and Brittle-burst on every E-Q catch."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-3 on Q-tip farm, then use W's unstoppable shield to absorb his double-shot poke","Land E into your own Q-pillar for the terrain knock-up so his E-dash can't kite the stun","Reach 6 and first item, then R-catch him and W-Brittle detonate before he repositions"],"foe":["Poke you with passive double-shot and Q before you have your shield or combo","Hold his E-dash to break your E-Q knock-up and kite backward out of W range","End the lane and roam before your tank items and Masterwork upgrades make him useless into you"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Lucian and you just have to accept it — you have no shield, no combo and no mana, while his passive double-shot and Q whittle you every time you walk up for a minion. Do not contest last-hits in his auto range; take them with the tip of your Q from max distance and let him push. The trap is committing an E into him before 3, when there's no terrain to stun against and no W shield to survive the return fire. Survive to W and the lane starts to turn.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where you climb back to even. W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield mean you can finally tank a poke trade and answer it, and a second combo point lets you punish him if he steps up to farm — E into your Q-pillar for the knock-up, then W-Brittle while he's airborne. The key is your E must collide with terrain (his own body won't do it), so drop the Q-wall first or aim into a lane wall. Bait his E-dash; if he burns it to break your knock-up, your next E-Q catches him clean.","late":"This is your half of the lane. Once you have a tank item and especially after the Masterwork upgrades at 13, his double-shot DPS stops meaning anything into your stacked armor and health — you simply walk him down. Catch him with R's charging knock-up or an E-Q against a wall, detonate Brittle with W, and his lack of a second escape after E means he's dead. Don't let him just farm and scale into a sidelane; force the all-in on every cooldown of his E and end it.","whys":["Lucian's passive double-shot and Q poke you down while you have no shield, no combo and no mana — pure last-hit survival.","He keeps poking with double-shot and Q and you still have no W shield to trade back; just farm at Q range.","His range and E-dash still out-trade you, but your fresh W lets you absorb a step-up — the lane is starting to stabilize, not yours yet.","Your second combo point and W shield make trades even — punish his farm step-ups with E into Q-pillar but respect his E-dash kite.","R's double knock-up plus E-Q terrain stun finally beats his all-in, but a clean E-dash can still break your combo, so it's skill-decided.","Your first tank item lets you eat his double-shot and force trades, yet a fed Lucian still kites — whoever lands their cooldowns owns it.","Your stacked armor, health and Masterwork upgrades make his auto-DPS irrelevant; one E-Q knock-up into W-Brittle kills an escape-less Lucian."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"malphite","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Malphite","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your W (Bellows Breath) percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade into his armor freely since it deals max-HP magic damage his stacked armor can't reduce."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Unstoppable Force) is the lane's scariest button — it knocks you up for a guaranteed all-in or gank setup, and his ult is up before your team value matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"A Sunfire/Heartsteel and boots turn you into a durable W-poke bully who shrugs off his Q (Ground Slam-empowered) pokes."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and second item give your whole team a gold lead his single-target engage can't match."}],"wants":{"you":["Land W (Bellows Breath) on cooldown — its percent max-HP magic damage ignores his stacked armor and applies Brittle","Set up E (Searing Charge) into your own Q (Volcanic Rupture) pillar for an unmissable knock-up plus Brittle detonation","Reach 2 items and your level-13 Masterwork upgrades to convert lane into a team-wide gold lead"],"foe":["Hit his Q (Seismic Shard) slow poke to chip you while you're mana-starved at levels 1-2","Land his R (Unstoppable Force) knock-up at 6 to guarantee an all-in or gank","Stack armor and W (Thunderclap) to win a sustained auto-trade you can't enter"]},"early":"Malphite is an armor tank, so the one thing he can never reduce is your W (Bellows Breath) — it deals percent max-HP MAGIC damage and applies Brittle no matter how much armor he stacks. He concedes the AP duel, but you're both weak and mana-hungry levels 1-2, so just farm through his Q (Seismic Shard) poke and don't burn mana chasing. By level 3 with Q and W up, his armor is a non-factor and you trade back at will.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are even — you both want to set up, and your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up is strong but his W shred and Q slow let him trade respectably, so it's a skill window. Then 6 belongs to him: his R (Unstoppable Force) is a long-range guaranteed knock-up that wins the flat all-in and sets up ganks before your team value comes online. Hold your E and don't get walled into his ult — bait the R, then punish the long cooldown.","late":"Once you have 2 items and especially your level-13 Masterwork upgrades, you pull ahead for good — your free item upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead his single-target engage simply can't answer. His R is a one-shot teamfight tool; yours is a double knock-up that, with your team-wide value, ends fights. Keep W'ing him in skirmishes; his armor never touches your magic damage.","whys":["You're both feeble level 1, but his armor-stacking does nothing against your kit and you out-scale his lane presence the moment W comes online.","Still no real combo for either of you, but his Q poke is mana-negative for him and your W will ignore everything he builds — the lane is already tilting your way.","With Q and W up, your W's percent max-HP magic damage and Brittle blow straight through his stacked armor — he simply can't trade the AP exchange.","Levels 4-5 are genuinely even: your E-Q pillar knock-up is lethal but his W shred and Q slow let him trade back, so it comes down to who lands their setup.","His R (Unstoppable Force) is a guaranteed long-range knock-up that wins the flat all-in and enables ganks before your teamfight value exists — respect it.","First-item window is a coin flip: your Sunfire/Heartsteel bully spike is real, but his R is still up and can flip any extended trade.","Your level-13 Masterwork upgrades and 2-item durability hand your whole team a gold lead his single-target engage can never out-value."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"maokai","win":["Skill","Maokai","Maokai","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Maokai owns this window — his sapling W-dash root and Q knockback out-trade you before your Bellows Breath shield and Brittle come online at 3."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up flips the lane: ram him into your own Q pillar with E and the unstoppable W exhale chunks his max HP through his sustain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots turns you into the durable bully — W-poke chips faster than his saplings and passive heal him back."},{"when":"Late","text":"As an immobile teamfight tank he can never escape your E-Q knock-up, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 out-gold his itemization."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive his level 2-3 sapling poke and reach Bellows Breath so W's percent-HP exhale and Brittle out-sustain him","Hit Level 6 and use R-then-E to ram him into a Q pillar for the double knock-up all-in","Get your first tank item and W-poke him faster than his passive and saplings can heal back"],"foe":["Use sapling-empowered W root dash and Q knockback to win the level 2-3 all-in before your shield exists","Stack his passive sustain and saplings to negate your W chip and farm even into your spike","Match your scaling as a fellow tank and look to roam/teamfight since he can't 1v1 your CC late"]},"early":"Maokai owns the first levels here and you just farm — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved while his sapling-empowered W root dash and Q knockback let him bully you off CS. Don't step into his sapling field for a last hit at 1-2; eat a little poke and wait for Bellows Breath. Once you have W at 3 you can finally exhale percent-HP damage and apply Brittle to trade back, but until then respect his level 2 all-in — his root plus saplings will out-DPS you before your shield exists.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even out as you get a second combo point and can punish him with E into a Q pillar for a knock-up — but he's immobile, so he can't dodge it the way a duelist would. Level 6 is your window: pop R for the charging knock-up, then E-dash into the elemental to redirect it, and your W stays unstoppable through his root so he can't peel the all-in. Bait his W root dash — once it's down he has no escape from your E-Q stun chain.","late":"This stays in your favor late, which is rare for a tank mirror — Maokai is immobile and trades evenly, so he can never escape your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up or your R double knock-up the way a kiter would. Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team an effective gold lead his itemization can't match, and your W keeps chipping his max HP faster than his passive heals. Just don't let him out-roam you into picks elsewhere — win the sidelane and your CC anchors every fight.","whys":["You're one of the weakest level-1 toplaners with no shield or combo, but Maokai also can't all-in yet — just last-hit and set up the lane.","Maokai's level 2 sapling-empowered W root dash and Q knockback out-trade you cleanly before your Bellows Breath shield exists.","He still edges you at 3 — his saplings and passive sustain heal through your first W exhale faster than you can punish.","With a second combo point you can E into a Q pillar for a knock-up he's too immobile to dodge — the lane levels out.","Your R charges in for a double knock-up and W stays unstoppable through his root, winning the all-in past his sustain.","Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots makes you the durable bully — W-poke chips his max HP faster than his passive heals.","As an immobile tank he never escapes your E-Q knock-up, and free Masterwork upgrades at 13 out-gold his single-target presence."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"mel","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once W (Bellows Breath) is online its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you walk through her Q poke and trade back through her chip."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) into E-Q wall gives a double knock-up that chains Brittle burst — her R reflect can't save her once she's airborne and stunned."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots turns her Q poke into free farm — you brick-wall her with Q terrain and W-poke her off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Mel's biggest window: pre-W you have no shield and no combo, so her ranged Q chips you freely while you only last-hit."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable shield+percent-HP exhale so her Q poke stops mattering","Land E into a Q pillar (or her own minions) for the knock-up-Brittle chain before she can R-reflect","Itemize Heartsteel/Sunfire and walk the wave down, tanking her poke into free CS"],"foe":["Land Q pokes from max range and kite back so she never eats your W exhale or E-Q","Hold her R to reflect your committed E-Q-R burst back into your face","Stall lane even and scale her W/E zone-and-execute into mid-game teamfights"]},"early":"Mel out-ranges you hard at levels 1-2 — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so just last-hit and eat a bit of her Q poke rather than walking up. Everything flips at 3 when W (Bellows Breath) comes online: it's unstoppable, shields you, and deals percent max-HP, so you can stride through her poke and exhale her face. Don't throw E blind into her — bait her Q cooldown first, then commit.","mid":"This is where you take over. E (Searing Charge) into your own Q pillar — or into the minion wave behind her — knocks her up, and W's Brittle makes your follow-up autos hit like trucks. At 6, R adds a long double knock-up that chains straight into your E-Q; watch for her R reflect and don't dump your whole combo into it, but airborne-and-stunned she can't activate it in time. Her Q poke can't out-pace your W sustain once you're trading on your terms.","late":"You keep the edge unusually well here for a tank lane — Mel is squishy and your E-Q-R chain one-shots her positioning if she steps up. Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team a gold lead while she's a single-target poke threat. Respect her R reflect on your engage and her W/E zone in fights, but a flanking R knock-up deletes her before she reflects anything.","whys":["Pre-W you have no shield and no combo while Mel pokes you with ranged Q — it's even only because you can still farm safely at Q range.","Still no W: she chips you with Q and you can't punish, so you just soak CS and wait for level 3.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield lets you walk through her Q and trade back hard.","Second combo point lands and you can E into a Q pillar for a knock-up that her ranged poke has no answer to.","R (Call of the Forge God) chains into E-Q for a double knock-up — airborne and Brittle-stunned, she can't R-reflect in time.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a wall-building lane bully who tanks her Q and W-pokes her off the wave.","You stay ahead — your E-Q-R one-shots her squishy frame and your level-13 Masterwork upgrades out-value her single-target poke."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"mordekaiser","win":["Skill","Mordekaiser","Mordekaiser","Skill","Mordekaiser","Mordekaiser","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath) you finally trade back — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield blunt his Q isolation slam."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Morde's R (Realm of Death) is his hardest window — he drags you into a 1v1 where he steals your stats and your CC means nothing alone, so never be low when his R is up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His Riftmaker/Rylai spike lets him stick and out-sustain his Q poke through your W shield — hold your E-Q until he over-extends."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 plus a second tank item make you the unkillable anchor, while his single-target R only nets one kill in a fight you out-number."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm through levels 1-3 with W percent-HP pokes and avoid eating his E-pull into Q isolation","Bait his W shield/heal and his R, then E-into-Q-pillar knock-up him after his realm cooldown","Reach 2+ items and 13 so your Masterwork upgrades and durability turn the lane and fights"],"foe":["Land E (pull) into an isolated Q slam for the bonus-damage burst before your W comes up","Use R (Realm of Death) to drag you into a 1v1 where he steals your stats and your team can't help","Stack Riftmaker/Rylai to stick and out-sustain through W, snowballing before your scaling lands"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are rough — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so don't contest his E-pull into an isolated Q slam, just hold range and farm. The moment you hit 3 and have W (Bellows Breath), you can finally answer: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you poke back and shrug his Q burst. Don't get yanked by his E into the wall — that's the whole isolation combo that bursts you before W is up.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you start to even it with a second combo point — punish him stepping up to Q-poke by E-ing into your own Q pillar for a knock-up, then W-Brittle for the burst. But level 6 is HIS window: his R (Realm of Death) drags you into a stat-stealing 1v1 where your team can't peel and your CC doesn't matter solo. Never be low or push past river when his R is up — bait it, survive the realm, and the duel swings back to you afterward.","late":"This is where you take over. At 13 your Living Forge Masterwork upgrades give your whole team an effective gold lead, and two tank items make you nearly unkillable through his AP burst. His R only deletes one target — in a real teamfight you out-number it with your E-Q knock-up and R double knock-up chaining Brittle. Group, don't get caught alone for his realm, and let your durability and team-wide item edge win the game.","whys":["You're both weak level-1s, but you have no shield or combo yet — just last-hit and don't get pulled by his E into an isolated Q.","His Q does bonus isolated damage and you still have no W to answer — he wins any short trade at 2.","He out-pokes you with Q and out-sustains with W heal before your combo is online, edging the level-3 window.","Your W percent-HP poke and first E-Q knock-up let you trade back evenly once you have two combo points.","His R (Realm of Death) drags you 1v1 and steals your stats — your CC means nothing solo, so he owns 6.","His Riftmaker/Rylai spike lets him stick and out-sustain through your W shield before your tank items land.","Your 13 Masterwork upgrades and double-tank durability make you the anchor while his single-target R nets only one kill."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"nasus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Nasus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have W you exhale percent-HP fire and apply Brittle while unstoppable — Nasus can't wither-kite you out of the trade."},{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"E into your Q magma pillar knocks him up and detonates Brittle — punish every time he walks up to last-hit a Q stack."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R's double knock-up plus E-Q chains enough CC that a wither can't save him in an all-in or gank."},{"when":"Late","text":"A free-farmed Nasus with stacked Q and R lifesteal/size out-duels your single-target presence — don't 1v1 him at 2+ items."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny Nasus Q last-hits with Q poke and W percent-HP fire so his stacks stay low","Land E into your Q pillar for the knock-up and Brittle detonation before he hits an item","Snowball your lead into towers so his free-farm scaling never comes online"],"foe":["Wither your move and attack speed to walk away from your W-E range and farm safely","Free-farm Q stacks and E armor-shred until his single-target damage out-duels you","Reach R lifesteal and size to win extended even-gold duels at 2+ items"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you're both weak and just farming — you have no shield or combo and you're mana-starved, so don't force anything. The lane turns at 3 when W comes online: it's unstoppable, so his wither can't kite you out of it, and the percent-HP fire plus Brittle lets you trade back while denying his Q stacks. Contest his last-hits with Q poke and accept that this is a starving, slow phase for you both.","mid":"This is your window. With a second combo point you E into your own Q magma pillar for a knock-up, then auto into the Brittle for bonus damage — every time he steps up to last-hit a stacked Q, punish it. At 6 your R adds a long-range double knock-up; chained with E-Q he simply can't wither his way out of a full all-in, and you set up clean ganks. Keep his stack count low and shove him off the wave.","late":"Respect the scaling. A Nasus who free-farmed reaches a point where stacked Q, E shred, and R lifesteal/size out-duel your single-target presence in an even-gold 1v1 — your armor stacking does nothing against his ramping on-hit. Don't solo him at 2+ items. Your value flips to the teamfight: your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team a gold lead, and your E-Q-R CC chain locks him down for your carries instead of dueling him yourself.","whys":["You're both among the weakest level 1s — no shield, no combo, mana-hungry — so just deny his Q last-hits and farm.","Still even with one point each: he can wither but has no all-in, and you have no W yet to punish it.","Your W comes online unstoppable, so his wither can't kite you out of the percent-HP fire and Brittle — but his early Q stacks keep it close.","E into your Q pillar knocks him up and detonates Brittle every time he steps up for a stack — your first clear edge.","R's double knock-up plus E-Q chains through his wither and wins the all-in or gank.","Your tank/health first item lets you W-poke and tank trades, but his Q is starting to stack toward parity.","Free-farmed Nasus out-scales you: stacked Q, E shred and R lifesteal/size beat your single-target presence — don't 1v1, fight as a team."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"nautilus","win":["Skill","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"You both have no combo yet, but his auto-attack passive root lets him land a free auto trade while you have no shield — keep your distance and last-hit at range."},{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"His Q hook into E AOE plus passive root is a real all-in once he has mana; respect it and only W-poke when his hook is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R single-target knockup point-and-clicks you for a guaranteed CC chain — do not be caught without your W shield up when he hits 6."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 plus tank items make you the better fight anchor; you out-scale his single-target lockdown in the 5v5."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely to 3, then use W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield to chip him without eating his hook","Bait his Q hook out, then E into your Q-pillar for a knock-up trade while it's on cooldown","Scale to 13 for Masterwork upgrades and turn every teamfight with your E-Q and R double knock-up"],"foe":["Land Q hook and proc his passive root with autos to lock you for a full E AOE trade","Hit 6 and point-and-click R knockup to chain CC onto you with no skillshot to dodge","Get on top of you and stack his short cooldown CC so your telegraphed E-Q never connects"]},"early":"You're one of the weakest level-1s in the game and Nautilus isn't — his passive roots you off a single auto, so don't walk up to last-hit when he can step on you. Just collect CS with the range on your Q and accept chip. Once you hit 3 and have W, his hook becomes a two-way street: dodge or bait the Q, then his all-in stalls and you can W-poke his percent HP back.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where he edges you. His Q hook into E AOE with the passive root is a real lockdown combo once he has the mana for it, and at 6 his R is point-and-click — there's no skillshot to sidestep like there is with your E. Keep your W shield available whenever he's level 6 so you eat the knockup with armor and percent-HP mitigation up, and only commit your E-into-Q-pillar when his hook is down.","late":"This is where it flips your way. He's a single-target lockdown tank with no scaling — once you hit 13 your free Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead, and your E-Q wall knock-up plus R double knock-up out-anchor his one hook in a 5v5. Don't get caught alone where his Q-E-R chain can blow you up, but in the actual teamfight you're the bigger problem.","whys":["You're both weak and comboless at 1, but his passive root off one auto gives him the only real trade tool — it's a wash you respect.","His Q hook plus passive root lets him start a trade you can't answer until your W comes online next level.","With Q and W he has mana for a full hook-into-E AOE all-in, and your shield alone doesn't out-trade the lockdown yet.","His self-rooting CC chain punishes any step-up, and your telegraphed E-Q can't reliably land on a target sitting on top of you.","His R is a point-and-click knockup with no skillshot to dodge — he owns the all-in the moment he hits 6.","His tankier first item plus full CC combo still out-trades your single W-poke window in lane.","Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 and double knock-up out-scale his single-target hook — you become the better teamfight anchor."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"neeko","win":["Skill","Skill","Neeko","Skill","Neeko","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"With Q and W online you get unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, so her Q-bramble and tiny E-root poke stops free trading you down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R is her one real threat — if she lands the upfront stun (often after an E-root or off a clone), her AOE burst can chunk you before W's shield comes up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire with boots makes you a durable lane bully — you W-poke her squishy frame and walk through her Q poke she can't sustain through."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"You become the unkillable anchor: your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and R double knock-up shut down her pick attempts and turn her one engage into your win condition."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield so her Q-bramble poke stops mattering","Itemize Heartsteel/Sunfire and bully her squishy frame with W while tanking her Q","Land E-into-Q-pillar knock-up to set up Brittle burst and deny her R pick windows"],"foe":["Land E-root or R-stun on you so her clone-fed combo bursts before W shields","Poke you with Q-bramble while you're mana-starved early and shove you off CS","Avoid your E-Q telegraph and roam to set up picks on your team with her clone"]},"early":"Neeko's whole early is poking you with her Q-bramble and chipping you with the E-root while you're mana-starved with no shield yet — at levels 1-2 you just farm and eat it, you can't trade back. The lane flips at level 3: once W is up you get unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield, so she can't keep free-poking you down. Don't waste E chasing her clone or a dodge — bait her E-root, then step in with W to trade through it.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are a genuine coinflip — you have a second combo point and can punish an overextension with E-into-Q-pillar, but if she catches you with E-root into her Q she chunks you back. Respect level 6: her R is the one button that beats you, because the upfront AOE stun (off a clone or after E-root) can burst you before W's shield buffers it. Hold W for that stun window, don't blow it on poke, and she has no follow-up if her R whiffs.","late":"Once you hit your first item — Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots — this becomes your lane. She's squishy and can't sustain your W percent-HP poke, and your armor plus health soaks her Q chip while you walk her down. At 2+ items you're the near-unkillable anchor and she's a pick-mage with one engage: your E-Q knock-up and R double knock-up either deny her R or punish her for using it, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make your whole team's teamfights lopsided. Just don't facecheck her clone in fog.","whys":["She pokes with Q-bramble while you have no shield and no combo — last-hit with Q's tip and accept the chip, you can't trade back yet.","Still mana-starved with only Q; she keeps Q-poking you and you just farm and wait for W.","Her Q-bramble and E-root out-poke you the moment you step up — she edges this window before your W shield exists.","Coinflip: your E-into-Q-pillar punishes an overstep, but her E-root into Q chunks you back just as hard.","Her R is her real spike — the upfront AOE stun off a clone or E-root can burst you before W's shield comes up.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a durable bully — your W percent-HP poke wrecks her squishy frame and she can't sustain it.","You become unkillable and your E-Q and R double knock-up shut down her picks — out-itemized, her one engage just feeds your teamfight."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"olaf","win":["Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Skill","Skill","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Olaf walks you down with axe slows and lifesteal while you have no shield and no combo — concede CS and hug tower."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale and a shield to finally trade back into his axe poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Olaf's R makes him CC-immune and his axes deal true damage through your shield — but your R double knock-up and E-Q wall let you answer the all-in."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus your level-13 Masterwork upgrades flip the lane — you out-durable his lifesteal and become the teamfight anchor."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 with safe last-hits until W gives you unstoppable poke and a shield at 3","Land E into your Q magma pillar for a knock-up so your W exhale applies Brittle and your auto detonates it","Stack health/tank items and hit level 13 Masterwork upgrades to out-scale his lifesteal"],"foe":["Use axe slows and lifesteal to walk you down levels 1-2 before your W exists","Pop R for CC-immunity and true damage so your E-Q knock-ups and shield mean nothing in the all-in","Pick up axes off the ground to keep cooldowns short and chunk you in extended trades"]},"early":"Olaf owns the first two levels harder than almost anyone — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, while he slows you with axes and heals through your chip with lifesteal. Don't try to fight; last-hit at max range and accept the poke. At level 3 your W finally gives you a foothold: it's unstoppable so his slows can't stop the exhale, the percent-HP damage chunks him, and the shield blunts his axe trades. Until then, dodge his axe throws by walking perpendicular and never sit still in the slow.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are still his — a second axe point and his lifesteal mean he wins extended trades unless you catch him out of position. Your real answer is the E-into-Q combo: drop your magma pillar, dash into it with E for the knock-up, then W-exhale to apply Brittle and auto to detonate it. At 6, respect his R — it makes him CC-immune and his axes deal true damage that ignores your shield entirely, so a careless all-in into his ult loses. Bait the R or fight when it's down, and use your own R double knock-up to peel.","late":"This is where you take over. Olaf is a lane bully who falls off, and your scaling is the opposite — Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you a durable anchor his single-target lifesteal can't shred, and at level 13 your Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead. In teamfights his R only ignores CC for a few seconds; your E-Q wall and R double knock-up lock down everyone else. Don't 1v1 him under his ult, but in any 5v5 your durability and chained CC bury him.","whys":["Olaf walks you down with axe slows and lifesteal while you have no shield, no combo, and no mana — one of the worst level-1s in the game.","He keeps the slow-and-sustain pressure at 2 and you still have nothing to trade back with — just farm at range.","Even with W online his lifesteal and second axe point out-sustain your single exhale; you stabilize but he still edges the trades.","His axes out-poke you levels 4-5 and his lifesteal heals through your W chip unless you land a clean E-Q knock-up.","Skill window: your R double knock-up and E-Q wall answer his all-in, but his R gives CC-immunity and true damage through your shield — whoever uses their ult better wins.","Both spike here — your tank item lets you W-poke and tank trades, but his lifesteal and true-damage axes keep it a coinflip on cooldowns.","You out-durable his single-target lifesteal and your level-13 Masterwork upgrades plus chained CC make you the teamfight anchor he can't kill."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"pantheon","win":["Pantheon","Pantheon","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Pantheon's W point-click stun into Q spear combo is his hardest punish window — you have no shield or combo yet, so don't walk into stun range for a CS."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield blank his stun-into-Q burst and let you trade back through Brittle."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up wins the all-in his early kit can no longer answer — he has no dash to dodge your charging elemental."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike turns you into a durable W-poke bully right as Pantheon's spear damage falls off into items."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive Pantheon's level 1-2 W-stun lane and farm to your level 3 W shield","Land E into a Q-pillar knock-up to set up Brittle-amplified burst once he commits","Hit 6 and use R's double knock-up to punish his now-weak all-in"],"foe":["Stun you with point-click W and follow with empowered Q spear at levels 1-2","Use his passive to block your auto-attacks and win short trades before your shield","Snowball an early lead with R global ganks before he falls off into items"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Pantheon — his W is a point-click stun he chains into an empowered Q spear, and his passive blocks your autos, so you have no shield and no combo to fight back. Don't contest CS inside his stun range; eat a little poke and farm with the tip of your Q. The moment you hit 3 and get W (Bellows Breath), the lane changes: it's unstoppable, so his stun can't interrupt it, and the shield plus percent-HP exhale let you trade back through Brittle.","mid":"Once you have your second W point and E (Searing Charge), you can punish him for stepping up — E him into your own Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then Brittle-detonate with an auto. His passive auto-block means nothing when your damage is percent-HP W exhale and CC. At 6 your R seals it: the charging elemental's double knock-up wins any all-in, and Pantheon has no dash to dodge it once your E-Q is set up.","late":"This only gets better for you. Pantheon is an early bully who falls off hard into items, while your first tank item makes you a near-unkillable W-poke anchor and your Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team a gold lead. His R global can still roam, so ward and don't let him snowball a sidelane — but in a straight fight he can't kill you anymore, and you out-teamfight him every time.","whys":["Pantheon's point-click W stun into empowered Q spear bursts you before you have a shield or combo — give up CS at stun range.","He still owns the short trade — his passive blocks your autos and his Q out-pokes your manaless level-2 kit.","Your W (Bellows Breath) is now up: unstoppable through his stun, shielded, and the percent-HP exhale lets you trade back evenly.","Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes his step-ups, and Brittle amplifies the follow-up burst his passive can't block.","R's double knock-up wins the all-in outright — Pantheon has no dash to escape your charging elemental.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a durable W-poke bully exactly as his spear damage drops off.","You're a near-unkillable teamfight anchor with free Masterwork upgrades while Pantheon hard-falls-off into the late game."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"poppy","win":["Poppy","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Poppy owns the open levels — her Q knockup-tipped slam and passive shield out-trade your shieldless, comboless level 1 while you just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield lets you trade back and shrug her Q poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up is the one window you clearly own — she has no dash escape and her W only blocks YOUR E dash, not your ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both of you spike into durable lane bullies; her E-into-wall stun answers your E-Q every all-in, so trades stay even."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield to stop conceding the lane","Land your level 6 R double knock-up while she has no dash to escape it","E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up before she W-blocks the dash"],"foe":["Use W to eat your E dash so your E-Q knock-up combo whiffs entirely","E you into a wall for the pin-stun and follow with Q knockup to win short trades","Trade evenly into mid-game and use R knockback to peel your engages in fights"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Poppy here — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so you just farm and eat a little of her Q poke. The lane evens out at 3 when W (Bellows Breath) comes online: it's unstoppable and shields you, so her Q knockup and passive-shield trades stop being free. Don't throw your E at her early — she'll W it, eat the dash, and your knock-up never lands.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are a coinflip — you can punish overextensions with E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups, but her W is always waiting to delete your dash, so only commit E when her W is down. Level 6 is your real window: R summons the charging elemental for a double knock-up and she has no dash to escape it, and her W only stops your E, not your ult. Bait her W on a fake step-up, then R and follow with E-Q.","late":"This stays a true 50/50 into the late game. You're the team-anchor with free Masterwork upgrades at 13, but Poppy is one of the few tanks who trades you evenly all game — her E pin-stun and R knockback peel your engages, and neither of you out-itemizes the other in a straight tank duel. Win it in fights, not the 1v1: you both want to be the one landing the game-deciding CC, so save your R for her carries, not for her.","whys":["You are shieldless and comboless at level 1 while her Q knockup and passive shield out-trade you — just farm.","Still even-to-behind — you have no W shield yet, so respect her Q poke and don't step into her E range.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back and neutralize her.","You can E-Q punish overextensions, but her W eats the dash — it's a skill matchup over whose cooldowns are up.","Your R double knock-up wins the all-in: she has no dash escape and her W only blocks your E, not the ult.","Both spike into durable bullies and her E-into-wall stun answers your E-Q — trades stay genuinely even.","Neither out-itemizes the other in a tank duel — it's decided by who lands their game-changing CC in fights."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"quinn","win":["Quinn","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Quinn's biggest window — her Harrier auto-procs and E vault-blind chunk you while you have no shield or combo to answer."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield that finally lets you trade through her poke and survive her all-in burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) charges across the lane: she can E her own knock-up away, so wall her escape with Q first, then ram for the double knock-up kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots make you a durable W-poke bully she can no longer whittle down faster than you heal and farm."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 farming with Q from max range, then stabilize the second W (Bellows Breath) shield is up","Pin her against a Q magma pillar so her E vault can't sidestep your E-Searing Charge knock-up","Hit your first-item spike and turn the lane into a W-poke grind she can't kite forever"],"foe":["Kite with Harrier move-speed and poke you down before your W shield exists at level 3","Save E vault to blind your auto and knock you back out of your E-Q combo range","Roam on her speed and waveclear to make picks elsewhere rather than fight your 6"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are hers — you have no shield, no combo, and her Harrier procs plus E vault-blind chip you while you can only farm. Don't walk up to throw a Q she'll just dance around with her move-speed; last-hit at max Q range and eat the poke. Everything changes at 3: once Bellows Breath (W) is up you're unstoppable mid-exhale, the shield blunts her burst, and the percent-HP fire actually punishes her if she steps into range.","mid":"This is where you take over. Your trade is E-Searing Charge into a Q magma pillar — the pillar gives you terrain to slam her against for the knock-up, then W exhales Brittle so your next auto chunks her. The whole game is denying her E vault an exit: wall behind her with Q so her knockback dash has nowhere to go. At 6, R charges her down — bait or pre-empt her E, then reactivate to ram for the second, bigger knock-up.","late":"You stay ahead here — Quinn is a tempo/roam champ, not a scaler, so she has no item answer to a fully-itemized Ornn. Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 hand your whole team an effective gold lead, and one E-Q-wall knock-up into R deletes her squishy frame in a fight. Just respect that she'll try to splitpush and roam rather than face your combo — track her, and don't let her trade your dead-end sidelane for kills across the map.","whys":["No shield, no combo, mana-hungry — she procs Harrier and E-blinds you while you can only last-hit. Concede the level and farm.","You get Q but still lack the W shield to answer her poke; she edges the trade but can't commit to a kill yet.","Bellows Breath (W) makes you unstoppable mid-exhale with a shield — you finally trade through her poke and survive her burst.","Your E-Searing Charge into a Q magma-pillar knock-up punishes any vault she mistimes, and W-Brittle amplifies the follow-up auto.","R (Call of the Forge God) charges her down for a double knock-up; wall her E exit with Q first and the all-in is lethal.","Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots turn you into a W-poke bully who out-sustains her chip and tanks every trade she starts.","She has no scaling item to reclaim the duel — your itemized combo and Masterwork upgrades at 13 keep you and your team ahead."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"renekton","win":["Renekton","Renekton","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Renekton's W stun and fury-empowered combos let him point-click bully you while you have no shield, no combo, and an empty mana bar."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your unstoppable Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and shield blunt his all-in and stop the free-trade snowball."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R's charging elemental plus a reactivated dash gives you a double knock-up that wins the all-in his fury combo used to win."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike turns you into the lane bully — you tank his combo and W-poke him while his item-fall-off begins."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive Levels 1-2 farming with Q range and don't burn mana while his fury is up","Stabilize at 3 with W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield to break his all-in cadence","Hit 6 and your first tank item to flip the lane — E-into-Q-pillar knock-up plus R double knock-up run him down"],"foe":["Win Levels 1-2 with the W stun and a fury-empowered Q/E combo before you have answers","Bait out your W or catch you mana-starved so his point-click combo trades for free","Snowball an early lead because he hard-falls-off once you survive to items"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are his — Renekton point-clicks you with W's stun and a fury-empowered combo while you have no shield, no combo, and barely any mana, so just farm with the tip of Q and refuse to trade autos into his fury. Don't waste E chasing; you can't catch a dash-empowered Renekton and you'll get stunned for it. The moment you hit 3 and have W, your unstoppable Bellows Breath shreds a chunk of his max HP and shields his return combo, which is the first time you make him think twice.","mid":"Now it tilts to you. With a second combo point you can E into your own Q-pillar to knock him up the instant he dashes in with W, and W shields whatever fury combo he answers with. At 6 your R charging elemental plus the reactivated dash gives a double knock-up that simply wins the all-in his early fury used to own — bait his W stun, then E-Q-knock-up into R and Brittle him down.","late":"This lane is over once you itemize. Renekton has no sustained threat after his fury combo is survived, and your first tank item plus Masterwork upgrades at 13 make you a near-unkillable anchor he simply can't kill in a straight 1v1. Don't let him roam or splitpush off an early lead — keep him pinned with W-poke and Q-pillar walls, and bring your item advantage to every teamfight.","whys":["Renekton point-clicks you with W's stun and fury combo while you have no shield, no combo, and no mana — just farm with Q range.","He still owns Level 2 with the empowered Q/E before your W exists; don't trade autos into his fury.","Your Q and W come online — unstoppable Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and a shield break his free-trade cadence and even the lane.","A second combo point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up the instant he dashes in, and W shields his fury answer.","R's charging elemental and reactivated dash double knock-up win the all-in his fury combo used to dominate — bait the W stun first.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike plus W-poke turns you into the bully exactly as his point-click combo starts falling off.","He has no sustained threat post-fury; your tank items and level-13 Masterwork upgrades make you unkillable in the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"riven","win":["Skill","Riven","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Riven's biggest window — she has her full Q-dash and W stun while you are mana-starved with no shield, so respect the level-2 all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online: unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield she cannot burst through mid-combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun chains CC her dash kit cannot escape."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus W-poke turns you into a lane bully who tanks her whole combo and trades back through Brittle."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable shield so her Q-dash combo cannot burst you mid-trade","Land E into your Q pillar (or her body) for the knock-up stun, then Brittle-amp with W and autos","Hit 6 and itemize — R double knock-up locks down a champion whose only defense is mobility"],"foe":["Hit her full three-Q-dash plus W stun combo inside your W cooldown to burst before your shield is up","Bait or sidestep your telegraphed E-Q so the knock-up whiffs and she dashes out with E","Snowball the level-2 window before you have shield, combo, and items"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Riven's, not yours — you have no shield, no combo, and you are mana-starved, so do not contest her three Q-dashes and W stun, just farm with the tip of your Q. The lane flips at 3 once W (Bellows Breath) is up: it is unstoppable, shields you, and chunks her percent max-HP while applying Brittle, so she cannot blow you up mid-combo anymore. Take the level-2 punish on the chin and last-hit; you only need to survive to your spike.","mid":"This is where you take over. With a second combo point you can E into your own Q magma pillar for a knock-up stun, then W and auto into Brittle for a huge chunk — her shield and E-dash cannot save her once she is airborne. The key is baiting her E dash out first; if she has burned her mobility, your E-Q lands clean. At 6 your R adds a long-range double knock-up that wins every all-in she starts.","late":"You keep this lane all game — unlike a scaling mage, Riven is a bruiser who falls off, and your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 plus tank itemization make you near-unkillable while she struggles to burst you down. Your E-Q-R CC chain locks her out of fights no matter how clean her mechanics are. Just do not facecheck her looking for a reset combo when your E is down; itemize and your shield plus Brittle trades win every extended exchange.","whys":["Riven is strong level 1 but commits to her combo; you are weak with no shield, so just farm and neither of you should win a clean trade yet.","Her level-2 spike with full Q-dash and W stun beats a mana-starved, shield-less Ornn — respect the all-in.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online: unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield she cannot burst through, so you trade back and stabilize.","A second combo point lets you E into your Q pillar for a knock-up stun and Brittle-amp the follow-up through her dashes.","R double knock-up plus E-Q chains hard CC that her Q/E mobility cannot dodge — you own every level-6 all-in.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike plus W-poke makes you a lane bully who tanks her combo and trades back through Brittle.","She is a bruiser who falls off while your Masterwork upgrades and tank items make you unkillable — your CC chain locks her out of fights."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"rumble","win":["Skill","Rumble","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Rumble owns the first push — his Flamespitter (Q) out-DPSes your mana-starved early autos, so concede the wave and farm under tower."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes fully online — its unstoppable percent-max-HP exhale ignores his Flamespitter chip and your shield eats the overheat burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) lets you punish him the moment he drops his Equalizer (R) zone — knock him out of his own flames and W-Brittle detonate."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike turns you into a lane bully who tanks his Flamespitter and walks him down on his E-harpoon cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 so W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale poke ignores his Flamespitter chip and your shield blunts the overheat","Wall him with E into a Q-pillar knock-up when he steps up to Flamespitter the wave","Bait his Equalizer (R) zone then R-charge him out of it and W-Brittle detonate"],"foe":["Push with Flamespitter (Q) and chip you off the wave while you're mana-starved early","Land E-harpoon to slow you out of E-Q wall range and kite your telegraphed engage","Save Equalizer (R) to zone you off CS and deny your all-in windows"]},"early":"Rumble's the rare lane where you actually lose the very early push — his Flamespitter (Q) is free sustained DPS and you're mana-starved with no shield at levels 1-2, so just farm and take the chip. Don't trade autos into his overheat window. Once you hit 3 and have W (Bellows Breath), it flips: its unstoppable percent-max-HP exhale pokes him without entering his fight, and the shield soaks the burst when he commits an overheated Q.","mid":"This is where you take over. He has to step up to Flamespitter the wave, and that's your E (Searing Charge) into a Q-pillar knock-up — collide him into your own magma wall, then W-Brittle detonate for a chunk. At 6 your R answers his Equalizer: when he drops the zone to zone you, R-charge him straight out of the flames and chain the double knock-up. He has no hard escape once his E-harpoon and W move-speed are down.","late":"Lane stays yours but late game is genuinely even — Rumble's Equalizer (R) is one of the best teamfight ults in the game and his AP percent-poke matters in fights. Your edge is your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and being the unkillable anchor that walks through his flames to reach his backline. Don't 1v1 him in his Equalizer zone; force the fight where your CC chain lands before he carpets the ground.","whys":["He's mana-starved level 1 too, but his Flamespitter chip edges a no-shield Ornn — last-hit and don't contest the push.","Rumble owns level 2 outright: Flamespitter (Q) out-DPSes your early autos and you have no combo yet, so farm under tower.","Your W (Bellows Breath) unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield neutralize his Flamespitter and let you trade back evenly.","Second combo point lets you E into a Q-pillar knock-up when he steps up to push, punishing his Flamespitter range.","R (Call of the Forge God) charges him out of his own Equalizer zone for a double knock-up he can't dash out of.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike tanks his Flamespitter and lets you walk him down on his E-harpoon cooldown.","Even late: your free Masterwork upgrades and durability balance his Equalizer zone and AP poke in extended games."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"ryze","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ryze"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath gives unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield his Q-E root combo cannot interrupt — start trading back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar gives you a long-range catch he has no dash or stun to escape — your hardest all-in window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots makes you a durable lane bully who eats his poke and W-pokes him off the wave."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Ryze's biggest threat window — Archangel's plus his Q reset spam turn him into a ranged raid-boss who roots and bursts you before you reach W range."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 and trade with W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale through his root combo","Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up, then detonate Brittle with autos","Hit your level 6 R catch and snowball before Archangel's stacks let him scale"],"foe":["Land the Q-E root combo from max range and kite back before your W-E reaches him","Stack mana and farm safely to Archangel's and Tear so his Q resets come online","Drag the game to even-gold late where his ranged poke out-itemizes your single-target CC"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you are one of the weakest toplaners alive — no shield, no combo, mana-hungry — so just farm and eat a little of his Q poke without trying to fight. The trap is his Q-E root: if he lands it he gets a free combo, so hug minions and don't walk into a forward Q. At 3 your Bellows Breath (W) flips it — you become unstoppable mid-cast, so his root can't cancel your exhale, and the shield blunts his burst.","mid":"This is your window. With a point or two in your combo you can E into your own Q pillar to knock him up, then auto for Brittle bonus damage — he has no dash and only a short hop, so a clean E-Q is a guaranteed stun on him. At 6 your R adds a long-range double knock-up that catches him out of position before he can W-root and kite away. Force every all-in here while his Archangel's is unbuilt — his poke can't out-damage your W sustain pre-items.","late":"Ryze is the textbook scaler this whole lane is racing against — once he has Archangel's, Tear stacks and his Q reset spam online, he becomes a ranged raid-boss who roots you from outside your W-E range and bursts you down before you close. Your single-target catch matters less when he has a shield, a self-peel root and realm-warp escape. Win it early: snowball the 3-to-6 window and end before his items let him kite you forever.","whys":["Ornn has no shield, no combo and is mana-starved at level 1 — but Ryze is a squishy melee-range caster here too, so neither side can commit; just deny last-hits.","Still no real combo for you, and Ryze's Q-E root needs mana he doesn't have yet either — trade poke and watch his root range.","Your W (Bellows Breath) is unstoppable mid-cast and shielded, so his Q-E root can't interrupt it and the percent-HP exhale out-trades his poke.","A second combo point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock him up and detonate Brittle with autos — he has no dash to dodge the telegraph.","R's long-range double knock-up plus E-Q catches a dashless Ryze who can only W-root and try to kite, winning the all-in.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you durable enough to walk through his poke and W-poke him off the wave before his items come online.","Ryze out-scales hard — Archangel's plus Q reset spam turns him into a ranged poke raid-boss who roots and bursts you before you reach W range."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"sejuani","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 4-5","text":"Your second E point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up her before she has her own engage online — your cleanest punish window."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up beats her single R stun in a raw all-in and turns any jungler gank lethal."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus W's percent-HP poke makes you the bigger lane bully through her cooldowns."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two immobile tanks scaling on free Masterwork upgrades — the lane goes even and it becomes a teamfight CC-chain contest."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your own Q-pillar for the knock-up, then W-Brittle to amplify the burst","Own the Level 6 window where your R double knock-up out-CCs her single R","Use W's unstoppable percent-HP poke to win the slow tank trade and out-bully her"],"foe":["Land her E stun off a Frost Armor permafrost proc to lock you mid-combo","Stack permafrost passive with autos and W's percent-HP to trade your HP down","Hold her R AOE stun for a jungler dive rather than spending it in lane"]},"early":"Two immobile mana-starved tanks farming — neither of you wins level 1, so just last-hit and watch her permafrost stacks. Her Frost Armor passive and E stun mean don't walk into auto range while she has it charged or she locks you for a free trade. You have no combo until Q and W, so don't throw a naked Q she can just walk through; W's unstoppable shield is your only real answer to her poke before 3.","mid":"This is your edge. With a second E point you can E into your own Q-pillar to knock her up, then W for the Brittle percent-HP detonation — she has no dash to dodge the telegraph and no shield to eat it. At 6 your R is a double knock-up that beats her single R stun straight up, so own all-ins here and punish any time she steps to permafrost you without her E ready.","late":"Two scaling tanks living on free Masterwork upgrades — the raw 1v1 flattens back to even and it becomes a CC-chain contest in teamfights. You out-value her with your level-13 item upgrades for the whole team, but she chains her permafrost-into-R AOE stun better into a grouped fight. Don't try to solo-kill her late; win it by landing your E-Q-R combo on her carries, not her.","whys":["Both of you are weak mana-starved level-1 tanks with no combo — it is a pure farming stalemate.","Neither has a real all-in at 2; her E stun off permafrost trades evenly with your W shield.","Once you have Q and W you stabilize, but she has Frost Armor and her E stun — it stays a coin-flip trade.","Your second E point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and W-Brittle her before her engage comes online.","Your R is a double knock-up that out-CCs her single R stun, so you own the level 6 all-in and gank setup.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire and W percent-HP poke make you the bigger bully, but she itemizes durably too — a slim edge.","Two immobile Masterwork-scaling tanks even out in the 1v1; it becomes a teamfight CC-chain contest, not a lane duel."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"sett","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Sett"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Sett has no Haymaker (W) or grab (E) yet, so his only trade is the passive double-punch — auto him through it and shove, you contest these levels better than most tanks."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once Sett has W stored he can true-damage smash you for chunks if you eat his right-fist punch — keep your W (Bellows Breath) unstoppable shield ready to soak the Haymaker."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up beats his R suppress in a raw 6v6 all-in — bait his ultimate, peel it with W-unstoppable, then E-Q-pillar him into your charging elemental."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sett's biggest threat: a Bami's/Black Cleaver + grit lead lets his E-grab-into-W combo two-trade you flat, and his percent-true-damage Haymaker ignores your armor stacking."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 6 and bait his R suppress, then answer with your own R double knock-up and W-unstoppable","Use W (Bellows Breath) to soak his stored Haymaker as percent-HP poke while staying unstoppable through his E-grab","Win the durable mid-game and out-itemize him with free Masterwork upgrades before his grit trades scale"],"foe":["Land his E grab to lock you in place, then unload the stored true-damage Haymaker (W)","Bait out your W-unstoppable, then re-engage with his passive punches and grit-fueled extended trades","Hit his first-item grit spike and snowball the lane before your team-fight scaling matters"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are unusually winnable here for a tank — Sett has no Haymaker stored and no grab yet, so his only damage is the passive double-punch, and you can auto him back and shove the wave while you wait for your kit. Don't walk into a Sett who hasn't shown his W charge unloaded, though. The moment he has W (Level 3) his right-fist punch into a max-HP-percent, true-damage smash will chunk you, so once that's online keep your W (Bellows Breath) up to soak it while you're unstoppable.","mid":"From 3 onward this is a W war: his stored Haymaker is true damage that ignores your armor, but your W is percent-HP poke AND a shield, and being unstoppable means his E grab can't pin you mid-cast. Trade by walking up, eating an auto, W-ing through his Haymaker, then E-into-Q-pillar to knock him up and detonate Brittle. At 6 your R is your best all-in window — bait his R suppress, peel it with W-unstoppable, then redirect your charging elemental for the double knock-up. You own the 6.","late":"Lane stays favoured but the 2+-item window flips to Sett: his Haymaker is percent and true damage, so as he stacks health and grit items he two-trades through your armor stacking, and his E-grab-into-W combo punishes any E you miss. Your edge becomes team-wide, not the 1v1 — your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team an effective gold lead, so stop dueling him alone and turn your CC chain into team-fight value instead of greedy split trades.","whys":["Sett has no Haymaker (W) or grab (E) at level 1 — his only trade is the passive double-punch, and you can auto him back and out-shove, contesting this level better than most tanks.","Still pre-W and pre-grab for Sett, so his trade pattern can't punish you yet — walk up, deny his last-hits, and set up your level-3 W window.","His stored true-damage Haymaker comes online and chunks through your armor, but your W (Bellows Breath) soaks it as unstoppable percent-HP poke — the trade is genuinely even now.","It's a W-vs-W stalemate: his Haymaker ignores armor but your W shields and pokes, and his E grab can't pin you while you're unstoppable, so neither side cleanly wins.","Your R double knock-up beats his R suppress in the all-in — bait his ult, peel with W-unstoppable, then E-Q-pillar him into your redirected charging elemental.","His first-item grit spike trades evenly with your tank-item spike — his percent-true Haymaker offsets your durability, so this window is a coin-flip on execution.","Sett out-itemizes the duel here: his percent and true-damage Haymaker shreds your armor stacking and his E-grab combo punishes you — stop soloing him and turn CC into team-fight value."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"shen","win":["Shen","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1","text":"Shen's W blocks your Q-line autos and his Q-empowered autos out-trade you while you have no shield or combo yet."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield finally lets you trade back through his Q pokes."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up beats his point-blank taunt all-in, and your E-into-Q-pillar stun chains Brittle before he can W-block it."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both of you are unkillable teamfight anchors — his global R presence vs your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 keep the lane dead even."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield, then trade back through his Q autos","Land E-into-your-own-Q-pillar to knock him up and proc Brittle before his W can block it","Outlast his global R impact by being the harder-to-kill anchor with your free Masterwork upgrades"],"foe":["Use W (Spirit's Refuge) to block your Q-line autos every time you step up to trade","Land E taunt to drag you into his Q-empowered autos and reset your E-Q combo angle","Press global R to swing a fight elsewhere on the map while the lane stays even"]},"early":"Shen owns level 1 — his W (Spirit's Refuge) zones out your Q-line autos and his Q-empowered slash out-trades you while you have no shield, no combo, and a starved mana bar. Don't walk into his auto range to throw a Q he can just W-block; last-hit at Q-pillar range and eat the chip. Once you hit 3 and have W (Bellows Breath), you finally have an unstoppable percent-HP exhale and a shield to trade back — that's when this lane levels off.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your window. Your E (Searing Charge) into your own Q-pillar knocks him up and applies Brittle — dodge his E taunt first, then dash so terrain collision lands the stun before he can W-block your follow-up autos. At 6 your R double knock-up cleanly beats his point-blank taunt all-in; he has no dash to dodge it and his W only eats one auto, not the CC. Bait his W cooldown, then commit the full combo.","late":"This settles into a true even — two near-unkillable tanks who do their work in the fight, not the duel. Neither of you out-1v1s the other; his global R lets him swing fights across the map while your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 hand your whole team an effective gold lead. Don't try to force a solo kill you can't get — match his roam pressure with your own Brittle-amplified teamfight engage and let item value decide it.","whys":["Shen's W blocks your Q autos and his Q-empowered slash out-trades you while you have no shield, combo, or mana at level 1.","By level 2 you have Q to farm at pillar range but still no W shield — neither of you can commit, so it's a wash.","Your W (Bellows Breath) arrives — unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield let you trade back through his Q pokes.","A second combo point lets you punish his step-ups with E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups before his W can block the follow-up.","Your R double knock-up beats his taunt all-in — he has no dash to dodge it and W only eats one auto, not your CC.","Your first tank item makes you a durable W-poke bully, but his own item lets him taunt-trade evenly — the edge narrows.","Both of you are unkillable anchors: his global R presence offsets your free Masterwork upgrades, leaving the lane dead even."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"singed","win":["Singed","Singed","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Skill","Singed"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Singed proxies your wave and runs through your poison-immune fling range while you have no shield or combo — you just lose CS and concede the early levels."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar is the one combo that actually pins a Singed who normally cannot be caught by a single CC — this is your kill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Singed's Rylai/Liandry plus his W fling lets him kite your telegraphed E-Q; tank a clean W-poke off him but do not chase his poison trail."},{"when":"Late","text":"A drain-tank Singed with move speed and Mejai/Rylai runs you down and proxies forever — your single-target CC cannot lock a champion built to never be caught."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive to Level 6 and land R into E-Q-pillar to finally pin a champion no single CC catches","Use W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield to tank his fling-and-poison trades","Wall off his run-down with a Q magma pillar at a choke and detonate Brittle with E"],"foe":["Proxy your wave, deny CS, and avoid your E-Q range entirely with his move speed","Fling you into his poison trail and kite the cooldown of your telegraphed E dash","Drain-tank and outscale into a build that simply runs you down in every fight"]},"early":"Singed concedes nothing here — he proxies your wave and stays just out of your fling-immune W range while you are at your weakest, no shield, no combo, mana-starved. Do not chase him into his poison trail trying to land an early E; you have no kill pressure pre-3 and you just take poison + a fling for free. Last-hit what you can under tower and accept that you are farming, not winning, Levels 1-2.","mid":"Once you have your combo you can finally threaten him, but his W fling and move speed dodge your telegraphed E-Q if you commit blind. Bait his fling cooldown, then E into your own Q-pillar so the knock-up lands on terrain and Brittle detonates with your W's percent-HP exhale. Level 6 is your real window: R's double knock-up is the one piece of CC that actually pins a Singed, so save it for an all-in, not a poke trade.","late":"This is where Singed reclaims it. A fully built drain-tank with Rylai's slow and stacked move speed simply runs you down and proxies your map, and your single-target E-Q-R combo cannot reliably lock a champion designed to never be caught. Your team value stays high from Masterwork upgrades at 13, but in the straight matchup do not duel him in open ground — wall a choke with Q and only fight when he flings into your team's CC.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and are mana-starved while Singed proxies and kites your fling range — you just lose CS.","Still no real combo; his W fling and poison trail punish any step-up and your E alone cannot catch his move speed.","Q and W online let you trade back with unstoppable percent-HP poke, but he kites your telegraphed E — genuinely even.","A second combo point lets you threaten E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups, but his fling dodges it on cooldown — skill matchup.","R's double knock-up is the one CC that actually pins an uncatchable Singed — your hardest all-in window.","Your first tank item lets you tank his fling trades, but his Rylai/Liandry kite keeps it even — neither snowballs.","A drain-tank Singed with move speed and Rylai runs you down and proxies forever — your single-target CC cannot lock him."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"sion","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath) your unstoppable percent-HP exhale out-pokes his E shield-break and applies Brittle for free trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into reactivation gives a double knock-up that an immobile Sion cannot dodge — your cleanest all-in and gank setup of the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you the lane bully — W-poke him off the wave and tank his charged Q comfortably."},{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Sion's biggest window: a fully-charged Q knockup plus his passive zombie state lets him out-trade you while you are shieldless and mana-starved."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your Q magma pillar for the wall knock-up, then Brittle-detonate with autos and W","Reach Level 3 for W's unstoppable percent-HP poke that ignores his shields and applies Brittle","Hit 6 and use R's double knock-up to lock down an immobile Sion in an all-in or gank"],"foe":["Land a fully-charged Q knockup to start a trade while you are still shieldless early","Hit you with E to shred any shield/health and poke before your W comes online","Survive his weak lane and scale his tanky teamfight passive into the mid game"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are his, not yours — you have no shield, no combo and you are mana-hungry, so respect a fully-charged Q knockup and just last-hit through it. The moment you hit 3 with Q and W the lane turns: W is unstoppable, so his charged Q cannot interrupt your exhale, and the percent-HP burn plus Brittle out-trades his E shield-break poke. Don't waste E chasing — hold it to combo off your Q pillar.","mid":"This is your window. Sion is completely immobile, so your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up lands on him every time, and the Brittle it leaves lets your autos and W chunk him. At 6 your R reactivation double knock-up is a free lock-down on a champ with zero dashes — use it to all-in or to set a gank. His charged Q is your only real threat, and W's unstoppable frames let you walk through it mid-cast.","late":"You don't fall off here — both of you are teamfight tanks, but your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team an effective gold lead his kit can't match. The lane goes even because two tanks struggle to kill each other in a straight 1v1, so stop forcing the solo duel and convert your lane lead into objectives. In fights, save R to peel his charged Q-engage and chain your CC for your carries.","whys":["You are one of the weakest level-1 toplaners — no W shield, no combo, mana-starved — so a charged Q out-trades you; just farm.","Still shieldless with only Q, while his passive zombie state and charged Q knockup let him win an extended trade.","W comes online: unstoppable percent-HP poke walks through his charged Q and applies Brittle, beating his E shield-break.","Second combo point lets you punish with E into Q-pillar knock-ups, and an immobile Sion cannot dodge the wall stun.","R's double knock-up locks down a dashless Sion for a full all-in and is your strongest gank setup of the lane.","Your tank-item spike (Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots) makes you a W-poke lane bully who tanks his charged Q for free.","Two tanks can't solo-kill each other, so it evens out — but your Masterwork upgrades at 13 still tilt the macro your way."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you walk through his E pull and trade back through his Q poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R + E-into-Q-pillar: your double knock-up combo out-CCs his root and bursts him before R drain can stack souls."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire + boots: you tank his W-bomb and Q rotation and W-poke him off the wave as a durable lane bully."},{"when":"Lvl 6 (his)","text":"His R drain with souls is his only real out — if he catches you rooted by E in an extended AOE fight he reclaims sustain, so kill him before souls stack."}],"wants":{"you":["Use W's unstoppable to ignore his E pull mid-dash and exhale percent-HP through his shield","Land E into your own Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then auto for Brittle burst","Hit Level 6 and chain R double knock-up into your E-Q before his R drain stacks souls"],"foe":["Land E to pull you in and root you for his W-bomb and Q poke rotation","Stack soul fragments off his R drain in an extended fight to out-sustain you","Poke you down with Q from max range so you never reach W exhale distance"]},"early":"Swain pokes with Q and wants to land E to pull and root you, but you out-stat him once W (Bellows Breath) comes up at 3 — its unstoppable tag means his E pull cannot interrupt your exhale, and the shield blunts his Q poke. Levels 1-2 just farm with Q range and eat a little poke; you have no shield yet and you are mana-hungry, so do not facecheck his E. Once you have Q and W, walk up and exhale percent-HP back at him through his poke.","mid":"This is your window. You out-trade a pre-Rylai/pre-item Swain hard: E into your own Q magma pillar knocks him up, your autos go Brittle, and W chunks his max HP. Bait his E pull — when it is on cooldown he has no peel for your dive. At 6, R double knock-up plus E-Q lets you chain CC longer than his root lasts and burst him before his R drain can stack souls and heal him back.","late":"Lane is yours, but Swain is a drain-tank scaler — full-AP with souls and Rylai's he becomes hard to burst and out-sustains extended AOE fights, exactly where your single-target combo loses value. Close the lane and snowball your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 into a team lead before his soul stacks make him unkillable. Never get caught alone by his E root in a 5v5 where his R drain runs forever.","whys":["Swain pokes with Q but you both just farm early — you have no shield or combo and are mana-starved, so last-hit and do not eat his E pull.","Still even — he can poke with Q and threaten E, but neither of you can commit a kill without your level-3 tools.","W (Bellows Breath) makes you unstoppable through his E pull and shields his Q poke while you exhale percent-HP back — you trade up now.","Second combo point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and punish his step-ups; he cannot duel your Brittle autos pre-item.","R double knock-up plus E-Q out-CCs his root and bursts him before his R drain stacks souls to heal.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike lets you tank his W-bomb and Q rotation and W-poke him off the wave — force trades here.","Swain out-scales with souls and Rylai's: he becomes a drain-tank who wins extended AOE fights, so end before his late even-gold scaling takes over."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"sylas","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Sylas"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"With Q and W up your unstoppable Bellows Breath shield blunts his E-chain-dash gap-close and your percent-HP exhale out-trades his Q drain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up beats his all-in, but watch his R — he can STEAL your Call of the Forge God and turn the double knock-up back on you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire with boots makes you a durable lane bully who tanks his Q/W drain while W-Brittle poke chips him down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-AP Sylas reclaims the duel — his Q/W drain-heal sustains through your single-target combo and he kites your telegraphed E-Q."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your Q-pillar for the knock-up stun, then W-Brittle exhale to detonate amplified burst","Use W's unstoppable shield to eat his E-dash engage and trade back with percent-HP fire","Bank your item-anywhere passive into an early tank item and bully him on first-item spike"],"foe":["Drain you down with Q poke and W heal to out-sustain your W exhale trades","Land his E chain-dash stun to combo, then bait or steal your R with his ultimate","Reach 2+ AP items where his drain-heal and ranged poke kite your telegraphed E-Q"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you just farm — no shield, no combo, mana-starved, so don't contest his Q drain last-hits and keep your distance from his E chain-dash range. At Level 3 you stabilize hard: W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield mean you can eat his engage and trade back, and his Q poke can't out-sustain your W. Don't throw a raw E he can dash away from — set your Q pillar first so E into it stuns.","mid":"This is your window. Levels 4-6 your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up plus W-Brittle detonation out-trades a Sylas who has to commit his E and W to fight you. At 6 your R double knock-up wins the all-in — but his R STEALS ultimates, so if he ults you he gets your Call of the Forge God back. Bait his E, then combo when his dash is down; don't all-in while his R is up and yours is stealable.","late":"Sylas reclaims the duel at 2+ items — full-AP, his Q/W drain-heal sustains through your single-target burst and he kites your telegraphed E-Q with his dash. The lane was even because you owned the mid-game; late, your value shifts to teamfights where your free Masterwork upgrades and chained CC matter more than the 1v1. Don't try to solo-kill a fed Sylas — anchor fights and let your item lead carry your team.","whys":["Both of you are weak at level 1 — you have no shield or combo and he needs levels for his drain, so just farm and avoid his E range.","Still even at 2 — you're mana-starved without your W shield online and his Q drain pokes safely, so concede and last-hit.","Your Q and W come online — W's unstoppable shield eats his E-dash engage and your percent-HP exhale out-trades his Q drain.","Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up plus W-Brittle detonation punishes him whenever his E or W is down.","Your R double knock-up wins the all-in — just respect that his R can steal it, so fight when his ultimate is on cooldown.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a durable W-poke bully, but his drain-heal keeps it close — even window.","Full-AP Sylas out-sustains your single-target combo with Q/W drain-heal and kites your telegraphed E-Q — play for teamfights, not the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"tahmkench","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once W (Bellows Breath) is online its percent-max-HP exhale chunks Tahm through his grey-health and applies Brittle for a follow-up auto."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar gives you a CC chain his W self-eat cannot fully cleanse before you detonate Brittle."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel or Sunfire with boots turns your W-poke into a durable lane bully cadence Tahm's grey-health regen can't keep pace with."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tahm's W devour and R map roam let him out-utility you in even gold, and his percent-HP true bite ignores your armor stacking."}],"wants":{"you":["Land W (Bellows Breath) percent-HP exhale to apply Brittle, then auto for the bonus Brittle damage before his grey-health regens","Hit the E-into-Q-pillar knock-up so your Brittle detonates through his W self-cleanse window","Use R's double knock-up to lock him so he can't W-devour an ally or roam with R"],"foe":["Stack grey-health passive and W-devour out your trade damage to out-sustain your W poke","Land Q tongue stun to set up a slow trade or a gank, then disengage","Roam bot with R and scale his drain-tank utility past your single-target lane edge"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are rough like always — no shield, no combo, mana-starved — so just farm and don't throw a naked Q he can walk through while his grey-health passive eats the chip. Respect his Q tongue stun: if he lands it he gets a free trade or a flash-Q kill setup, so hold your E so you're never caught flat-footed. At Level 3 your W (Bellows Breath) flips it — the unstoppable percent-max-HP exhale chunks even his fat HP bar and slaps Brittle on him, so W then auto and you win the math his sustain can't refund fast enough.","mid":"This is your window. With a second combo point you can E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up, then W for percent-HP and Brittle, and the bonus damage on a knocked-up target shreds him before his grey-health and W-devour bail him out. At 6 your R double knock-up plus E-Q locks him long enough that his W self-eat cleanse can't save him — chain the CC, detonate Brittle, and your first tank item makes every W-poke trade lopsided. Bait his Q stun by faking the step-up, then punish the whiff.","late":"You win the lane bully phase, but Tahm is a drain-tank who scales into a problem you don't fully solve 1v1 — his W devour and grey-health let him out-last your single-target damage, and his percent-HP true bite on R chews through your armor stacking. Your edge becomes team-wide: free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make your whole team richer, so cash the lead into objectives and don't try to solo-kill a 2-item Tahm. Watch his R roams and ping bot — his map pressure is the thing that out-grinds your lane win.","whys":["You're one of the weakest level-1 toplaners and so is a passive Tahm — no shield, no combo, just farm and deny his last-hits.","Still no W, and his Q tongue stun can punish any greedy step-up — play for CS and dodge the stun.","W (Bellows Breath) gives unstoppable percent-max-HP poke plus Brittle that his grey-health regen can't fully refund — you trade up now.","A second combo point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and Brittle-detonate before his W self-cleanse triggers.","R's double knock-up plus E-Q chains CC longer than his W devour can cleanse, winning the all-in.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes W-poke trades lopsided and tanks his Q-stun trade comfortably.","Tahm's W devour, grey-health, and percent-HP true bite out-sustain your single-target damage and his R roams out-grind the lane — even in gold."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"teemo","win":["Teemo","Teemo","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath) its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back through his blind for the first time."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) gives a long-range double knock-up that lets you catch a Teemo who has no dash and pancake him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots makes you tanky enough to walk through E-poison ticks and W-poke him off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Teemo's biggest window: his Q (Blinding Dart) shuts off your autos and you have no shield or combo yet, so he free-pokes you."}],"wants":{"you":["Walk up under your minions and W-exhale him for percent-HP through the blind, since W is unstoppable and shields the poke","Hit Level 6 and use R + E-into-Q-pillar to pin a dashless Teemo against terrain for a stun","Rush a health item (Heartsteel/Sunfire) so his E-poison and dart chip mean nothing and your W out-damages him"],"foe":["Blind (Q) your auto right before you W or E so your Brittle setup whiffs","Kite back with passive move speed and E-poison stacks, never standing in W-exhale range","Stack R-shrooms on his side of the wall and at chokes so you can't roam or dodge his zone"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Teemo's. I have no shield, no combo, and I'm mana-starved, so his Blinding Dart (Q) plus poison (E) just chips me while I last-hit at max Q range. Don't throw Volcanic Rupture (Q) into auto range hoping to push — he'll blind the follow-up and kite. At Level 3 W (Bellows Breath) flips it: it's unstoppable and shields, so its percent-HP exhale pokes him back even through a blind. Just farm and wait for that.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where I take over. W out-pokes his dart because it shields and ignores the blind on the cast, and a second point in E (Searing Charge) lets me dash into my own Q-pillar for a knock-up if he sidesteps poorly. At 6, R (Call of the Forge God) is the kill button — he has no dash, so I ult, then E him into the pillar for a stun and W-Brittle the burst. Bait his Q blind, then commit the combo on its cooldown.","late":"I keep the edge here unlike most of my ranged matchups — Teemo doesn't out-scale me, he becomes a map nuisance. Once I have a health item my W eats his DPS and his R-shrooms are the real threat, not the 1v1. Don't facecheck brush near objectives where he's stacked mushrooms, and use my Q-wall to block his escape when I do catch him. Close the side lane before his shroom vision web locks down the map.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo, and no mana — his Blinding Dart (Q) cancels your autos and you can only farm at max Q range.","Still pre-W: his poison (E) and dart out-chip you and you can't shield it, so concede the level and last-hit.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its unstoppable shielded percent-HP exhale lets you trade back through the blind for the first time.","A second combo point lets you E into your own Q-pillar for a knock-up, punishing any Teemo who steps up to poison you.","R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up catches a dashless Teemo, and E-into-pillar stuns him on his blind cooldown.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike lets you tank E-poison ticks and W-poke him off the wave with no answer.","He doesn't out-scale you — your W and durability win the duel; only his R-shrooms matter, so respect mushroom walls."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"trundle","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and shield let you trade back and out-range his Q bite."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up + E-into-Q-pillar stun chain Brittle for a burst all-in his sustain cannot heal through."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire with boots turns you into a durable lane bully who W-pokes him off the wave."},{"when":"Late","text":"Trundle's R steals a percent of your resistances and his Q chips your AD — in extended even-gold games his drain-tank duel reclaims the 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Bellows Breath (W) percent-HP poke through his W speed zone before he closes to Q range","Set up E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups and detonate Brittle with your auto and R","Spike on your first tank item and W-poke him off CS so his drain-tank never stabilizes"],"foe":["Land Q bite to steal your AD and shrink your trade damage","Drop his E pillar to block your E-Q wall combo and disengage","Drag the game long so his R resistance-steal and sustain out-duel you"]},"early":"Trundle has no level-1 kill threat and neither do you — you're both mana-hungry and weak, so just farm and don't feed his Q bite free AD steals. Once you hit 3 with Q and W, your Bellows Breath gives unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield: chunk him from range instead of auto-trading where his Q drain wins. Watch for his W speed zone closing the gap to bite you, and back off the moment your mana is low.","mid":"This is your window. Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up sets up Brittle, and your W percent-HP poke out-damages his sustain when you don't let him land clean Q bites. At 6 your R adds a long-range double knock-up — chain E-Q-wall into R and your Brittle burst hits harder than his drain can heal. Watch for his E pillar blocking your E-Q wall slam, and force trades while your tank item makes you the bully.","late":"You win the lane and the early all-ins, but Trundle is a drain-tank built to reclaim long duels — his R steals a percent of your resistances and heals off it, and his Q keeps shaving your AD. In an extended even-gold 1v1 he out-sustains you. Lean on your real edge: your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 make you a teamfight anchor, so group and chain CC rather than dueling him alone in a side lane.","whys":["Neither of you has a level-1 combo or shield — you're both weak and mana-starved, so just farm and deny his Q bite free AD.","Still no W shield up; he can chip with Q drain, so respect his trade and last-hit at range.","Q and W online — Bellows Breath percent-HP poke and shield let you trade back and out-range his bite.","Your second combo point lets you punish steps-up with E-into-Q-pillar knock-ups he can't sustain through.","R's long-range double knock-up plus E-Q-wall chains Brittle burst his drain can't heal.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a durable W-poke bully who shoves him off CS.","His R resistance-steal and Q AD-drain out-sustain you in long even-gold duels — group and let Masterwork upgrades carry."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"tryndamere","win":["Tryndamere","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Trynd's crit autos and Fury-healed E gap-close out-trade your no-shield level 1 — concede the first two levels and just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Bellows Breath (W) comes online: unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield that blunts his spin, so you can finally trade back and Brittle him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Call of the Forge God (R) double knock-up wins the all-in and ignores his spin-kite — your cleanest kill window before his crit items."},{"when":"Late","text":"Once Trynd hits Berserker's Greaves plus Infinity Edge his crit DPS and Undying Rage (R) survive your full combo — he reclaims the duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 W so unstoppable percent-HP poke and the shield let you trade through his spin","Land E into your Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then Brittle-amplified W and R double knock-up at 6","Bank early CS leads and free in-lane item purchases (Passive) so your team out-itemizes him by teamfights"],"foe":["Fury-stack early with crit autos and his E gap-close to win levels 1-2 before your W exists","Spin-kite around your telegraphed E-Q so the knock-up whiffs and your CC is wasted","Scale to Infinity Edge and use Undying Rage (R) to survive your combo and reset the duel"]},"early":"Trynd owns the first two levels flat — you have no shield, no combo and you're mana-starved while his crit autos and Fury-healed E shred you, so don't contest, just last-hit. Everything changes at 3 when Bellows Breath (W) lands: it's unstoppable, shields you, and chunks him for percent max-HP while applying Brittle. Bait his E gap-close, then W into him so the spin damage hits a shield instead of your face.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your window. With a second combo point you can E into your own Q magma pillar to knock him up, auto for the Brittle bonus, and W to confirm the trade. At 6 your R is the closer — the charging elemental's double knock-up locks down his spin-kite and ignores the fact that he's slippery, and the Brittle chain means he can't just heal it off through Fury. Force the all-in before he buys crit.","late":"This is where it slips. Once Tryndamere has Berserker's Greaves and Infinity Edge his crit DPS out-paces your tankiness, and Undying Rage (R) lets him survive your entire E-Q-R combo at 1 HP for five seconds, then spin-heal back to full. Don't try to 1v1 a fed Trynd — your value is your team. Your Masterwork upgrades at 13 and your CC make you the teamfight anchor, so group, peel, and let Brittle-amplified knock-ups win fights instead of duels.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and no mana at level 1 while his crit autos and Fury-healed E out-trade you outright.","It is genuinely close at 2 — his Fury heal and gap-close are real, but you are one level from W flipping the trade.","Bellows Breath (W) gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield that eats his spin, letting you finally trade back with Brittle.","A second combo point lets you E into your Q pillar for a knock-up and Brittle-amplified auto he cannot kite through.","Your R double knock-up locks down his spin-kite and chains Brittle burst — your cleanest all-in before his crit items.","It evens out — your first tank item bullies the lane, but pre-IE Trynd farms safely and is still hard to fully kill.","Infinity Edge crit DPS plus Undying Rage (R) survives your full combo and resets the duel — don't 1v1 him, anchor your team instead."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"urgot","win":["Urgot","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Urgot"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Urgot owns the early levels — his Q shotgun-leg poke and W's sustained percent-HP DPS punish you while you have no shield and no combo, so just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Q-wall plus W's unstoppable Brittle poke comes online — you can finally trade back and W through his W stutter-steps."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun beats his all-in — bait his E flip, then chain CC before his R execute can stack fear."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"His Q/W percent-max-HP shreds your stacked armor and his R executes you below threshold — favor flips to Urgot in the extended duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 and reach Q+W so your unstoppable Brittle poke and shield blunt his shotgun-leg DPS","Land E into your Q pillar for the knock-up stun, then auto a Brittle target for amplified burst","Hit 6 and use R's double knock-up to win the all-in before his percent-HP out-trades you"],"foe":["Stack Q/W shotgun-leg hits to chunk your max HP before you have armor or shield","Land E flip to disrupt your E-Q combo setup and reposition for his W DPS field","Reach 2+ items so his percent-max-HP and R execute beat your tank stats in the sustained fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Urgot and you can't contest them — you have no shield, no combo, and his Q shotgun legs plus W's stutter-step DPS chunk you while you're mana-starved. Just farm and don't step into W range to throw a wasted Q. At 3 you stabilize hard: W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus shield lets you poke back and eat a trade, so start punishing when he commits his W and his legs are on cooldown.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are an even scrap — your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up wants to land, but his E flip can interrupt your setup and reposition you into his W field, so don't telegraph the dash. Six is your window: R gives a long-range double knock-up that beats his all-in, and chaining it into Q-wall stun plus a Brittle auto out-damages his shotgun legs. Bait the E flip first, then commit.","late":"This flips to Urgot. His Q/W deal percent-max-HP, which ignores the armor you stack to survive, and his R fear-and-execute finishes you below the threshold his sustained DPS pushes you to. You stay a teamfight anchor with your free Masterwork upgrades at 13, so your value is team-wide — don't try to solo-duel a fed Urgot, set up your CC for the 5v5 and let the gold lead from your free items carry.","whys":["Urgot owns level 1 — his Q shotgun legs poke for free while you have no shield, no combo, and a starved mana bar.","Still his level — his W stutter-step DPS out-trades you before your unstoppable W exists to answer it.","Skill swings here once Q+W are up: your unstoppable Brittle poke and shield let you trade back through his legs.","Even — your E-Q-pillar knock-up threatens him but his E flip can interrupt the setup, so it comes down to who lands first.","You own 6 — R's double knock-up plus a Brittle-amplified E-Q stun beats his all-in before his R can execute.","Your first tank item makes you a durable W-poke bully who tanks his shotgun-leg trades comfortably.","Urgot reclaims it — his percent-max-HP Q/W ignore your stacked armor and his R executes you in the sustained fight."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"vayne","win":["Vayne","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Vayne owns the opener — no shield, no combo, you eat tumble-empowered autos and bolt procs while you just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield lets you trade back through her kite for the first time."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into the rammed knock-up, then E into your Q pillar — a double-CC chain Vayne cannot tumble or condemn out of, and Brittle amps the burst."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Vayne's Silver Bolts percent-max-HP true damage shreds your stacked armor and HP — once she has her item spike she kites your telegraphed E-Q and wins."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive Levels 1-2 farming, then use W's unstoppable shield to trade through her tumble pokes from Level 3","Land E into your own Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then proc Brittle autos for the burst all-in","Hit 6 and chain R's double knock-up into E-Q so she can't condemn or tumble away"],"foe":["Kite with Q tumble + invis and stack Silver Bolts true-damage procs while you have no shield early","Save E condemn to cancel your E dash or stun you off your own Q pillar setup","Drag the game past two items where her percent-HP true damage out-duels your armor stacking"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are hers and there's nothing to fight about — you have no shield, no combo and you're mana-starved, so just last-hit and eat the chip from her tumble-empowered autos and third-bolt procs. Don't walk up to throw a Q she can simply tumble; farm with the tip of it. Everything changes at 3: once W (Bellows Breath) is up its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back through her kite — but only when you can actually connect.","mid":"This is your window. From 4-5 you can punish any forward tumble with E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up, then proc Brittle autos for real damage. At 6 your R is the equalizer: the rammed double knock-up plus E-Q is a CC chain she cannot tumble or condemn out of, and Brittle amplifies the follow-up. Bait her E condemn — if she burns it to cancel your dash, your next all-in is free. Hold your engage for when her Q tumble is on cooldown.","late":"Once Vayne has two items her Silver Bolts deal percent-max-HP true damage that ignores everything your armor and HP stacking gives you, and her tumble invis kites your slow, telegraphed E-Q. You don't win this 1v1 anymore — your job flips to being the team's anchor. Land R and E knock-ups to lock her for your carries and peel, don't chase her into a 1v1 where her true damage melts you. Close any lead you built around 6 before her item spike erases it.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and no mana at level 1 — Vayne's tumble-empowered autos and Silver Bolt procs poke you freely while you just farm.","Still no kit online for you, but she lacks her own all-in, so the lane is a low-stakes trade of her chip for your farm.","W (Bellows Breath) comes up — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield finally let you trade back through her tumble kite.","A second combo point lets you E into your Q magma pillar to knock her up and punish any forward tumble before she can reposition.","R's double knock-up chained into E-Q is CC she can't tumble or condemn through, and Brittle amps your auto burst — you own the 6 all-in.","Your first tank-health item makes you a durable W-poke bully who tanks her trades while she's still scaling toward her spike.","Vayne's Silver Bolts percent-max-HP true damage ignores your armor stacking and her tumble invis kites your telegraphed E-Q — she reclaims the late duel."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"vladimir","win":["Skill","Vladimir","Skill","Vladimir","Ornn","Skill","Vladimir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) online gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield to trade back through his Q-Transfusion sustain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q pillar is your one clean kill window before Vlad has pool up reliably and before his AP items come online."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike lets you W-poke and tank trades, but his Rylai's makes his E poke and slow far harder to dodge."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-AP Vlad pools your E-Q, ignores your armor with magic damage, and out-sustains everything — your team must answer him."}],"wants":{"you":["Land E into your Q-pillar for the knock-up so your W Brittle detonates burst before he can pool out","Use Level 6 R double knock-up to chain CC and force a kill while his pool cooldown is long","Reach teamfights with your free Masterwork upgrades and let your team focus Vlad instead of dueling him"],"foe":["Pool (W Sanguine Pool) the instant your E-Q knock-up lands to dodge the Brittle combo entirely","Poke you with E and Q-Transfusion under his own range so your mana-starved early can't punish","Scale to Rylai's plus Liandry's and kite your telegraphed E-Q while bursting you with magic damage"]},"early":"Vlad is also a weak level 1, but unlike you he sustains every trade with Q-Transfusion, so don't waste mana chunking him only to watch it heal back. You have no shield or combo until 3, so just farm with Q's tip and accept a little E poke — your big problem is he never runs out of resource while you're mana-starved. Once W (Bellows Breath) is up at 3 you can trade back with unstoppable percent-HP fire and a shield, but respect that he can simply Q-heal it and out-sustain a poke war.","mid":"Levels 4-5 favour him because his E poke and sustain grind you down faster than your single point of W can answer, and he has pool to dodge your only real engage. But level 6 is YOUR window: R summons a charging knock-up, and if you redirect it into E-into-Q-pillar you stack enough CC that his W pool can't save him if it's down. Bait the pool — once Sanguine Pool is on its long cooldown, R-E-Q with Brittle is a real kill. Don't throw the combo into an up pool or you've wasted everything.","late":"This is where Vlad takes the lane back hard. Full-AP with Rylai's and Liandry's he pools the moment your telegraphed E-Q animation starts, his magic damage walks straight through your armor stacking, and he out-sustains anything you bring. Your value flips to teamfights — your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 give your whole team a gold lead, so don't try to 1v1 him. Land R to peel and let your carries delete him while he's committed.","whys":["Both of you are weak level 1, but his Q-Transfusion sustains where you're mana-hungry with no combo — deny his last-hits and set up.","His E poke and Q sustain chip you down while you have only a single ability — he edges the resource war.","Your W (Bellows Breath) unstoppable poke and shield let you trade back, but his pool and Q-heal keep it even.","Pre-Rylai's he still out-pokes and out-sustains your two-point combo, and pool dodges your E-Q engage.","R double knock-up into E-Q pillar with Brittle bursts him if you bait the pool first — your cleanest window.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike tanks trades, but his Rylai's slow and ramping AP keep the lane contested.","Full-AP Vlad pools your E-Q, ignores armor with magic damage, and out-sustains you — let your team handle him."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"volibear","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"You concede the first two levels with no shield and no combo — Volibear's empowered Q dash and W bite-heal out-brawl you, so just farm with Q's magma line."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Q+W online: W's unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield blunt his W heal, so you trade back and stop getting bullied."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up beats his all-in — Call of the Forge God interrupts his Q-dash engage and his E stun before he lands them."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire spike: you become a W-poking lane bully and your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes every empowered-Q overcommit."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 farming with Q's line, then trade with W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale once you hit 3","Land E into your own Q magma pillar for the knock-up, then auto-trigger Brittle for bonus damage","Hit 6 and bait his Q-dash or E stun engage, then R double knock-up to flip the all-in"],"foe":["Win the level 1-2 window with empowered Q dash damage and W bite-heal before you stabilize","Stack W bites to heal through your W poke and out-sustain the brawl","Land E hand-of-the-god stun to lock you while his Q-dash and bites burst you down"]},"early":"Volibear owns the first two levels — he has empowered Q dash damage and W bite-heal while you have no shield, no combo, and a thirsty mana bar, so don't contest, just last-hit with the tip of your Q magma line. The lane flips at 3 the instant you get W: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale pokes him for free and the shield blunts his W-heal brawl. Trade with W when he steps up to last-hit, and don't whiff your E dash into open air — you want it landing into your own Q pillar.","mid":"This is your window. From 4-5 your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes every time he commits an empowered Q dash at you, and the Brittle from W lets your autos chunk him after the stun. At 6 your R double knock-up flat-out beats his all-in — when he engages with Q-dash or telegraphs his E hand-of-the-god stun, R the charging elemental to interrupt and flip it. His W heal can't out-sustain your W poke plus Brittle trades here, and your first item (Heartsteel or Sunfire) makes you the lane bully.","late":"You stay even-or-ahead because at 13 your free Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead — that's your real win condition, not the 1v1. Volibear scales and dives too, so don't try to solo-kill a tanky brawler who heals on every W bite; instead use your E-Q knock-up and R to peel and start fights. Don't get caught alone side-laning where his Q-dash plus E stun can chain you down without your team to follow up your CC.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and you're mana-starved — Volibear's empowered Q dash and W bite-heal out-brawl you at level 1.","Still no W to trade with, so his W bite-heal sustains through any poke you attempt — concede and farm with Q.","W comes online: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back and out-poke his bite-heal.","A second combo point means E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes his empowered-Q overcommits, and Brittle amps your autos.","R's double knock-up interrupts his Q-dash engage and E stun before they land — you win the 6 all-in outright.","Heartsteel/Sunfire turns you into a W-poke lane bully who tanks his brawl while Brittle trades grind him down.","He scales and heals on every W bite — the duel evens out, so anchor fights with R/E-Q rather than trying to solo him."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"warwick","win":["Skill","Warwick","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2-3","text":"Once you have W (Bellows Breath) its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back through his Q drain instead of just farming."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up plus your E-into-Q-pillar stun chains enough hard CC to blow up his R suppress window and win the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire with boots turns you into a durable W-poke bully whose shield eats his drain trades."},{"when":"Late","text":"In a long even-gold game Warwick's lifesteal-scaled drain and R suppress reclaim the straight duel as you lean teamfight anchor."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 W (Bellows Breath) so the shield and percent-HP exhale blunt his sustained drain trades","Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up-stun, then R to chain CC through his level 6 all-in","Build into your first tank item and become a W-poke lane bully who out-durables his chase"],"foe":["Stick to you with W (Blood Hunt) move speed and drain you down with Q sustain in extended trades","Catch you mid-E or after you blow combo and land R suppress for a guaranteed kill window","Scale his lifesteal/bonus-AD drain into the long game so his sustain out-duels your single-target presence"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are rough — you have no shield, no combo, and you're mana-starved, so a Blood Hunt Warwick who smells you low will stick with W move speed and Q-drain you. Just farm and don't trade into his sustain bare-handed. The lane turns at level 3: once W (Bellows Breath) is up, its unstoppable percent-HP exhale chunks him and the shield soaks his drain, so you can finally trade back instead of conceding.","mid":"This is your window. With a second combo point you can E into your own Q pillar to knock him up and stun, then W for Brittle so your autos hit harder — punish him any time he steps up to drain a minion. At 6 your R is the swing: its double knock-up plus your E-Q stun chains enough hard CC to interrupt or pre-empt his R suppress, so you win the all-in he wants. Bait his R, sidestep it with your CC ready, and detonate.","late":"You stabilize into a near-unkillable anchor, but in a long even-gold game Warwick's drain scales with his lifesteal and bonus AD — his sustained DPS and R suppress reclaim the straight 1v1 you used to win. Don't duel a fed Warwick in a side lane; your value is the teamfight, where your free Masterwork upgrades and self-comboed CC matter more than the solo kill. Group, peel, and let your CC chain set up your team rather than fishing for the splitpush duel.","whys":["You're both weak level 1, but you have no shield or combo and he can Q-drain — farm, don't fight.","His Blood Hunt W speed plus Q sustain wins the level-2 trade before your W comes online.","W (Bellows Breath) goes up — its shield and percent-HP exhale finally let you trade back through his drain.","E into your Q pillar knocks him up and applies Brittle, punishing any step-up his sustain can't out-trade.","R double knock-up plus your E-Q stun chains CC through his R suppress and wins the all-in.","Your first tank item makes you a durable W-poke bully whose shield eats his drain trades.","Long-game Warwick scales his lifesteal/AD drain and R suppress to reclaim the straight duel — group instead."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"wukong","win":["Wukong","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Wukong's level-2 Q armor-shred plus E-dash all-in is his cleanest kill window while you have no W shield and no combo yet."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — unstoppable percent-HP exhale plus a shield that eats his Q-empowered burst and applies Brittle."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R double knock-up is a hard counter to his all-in: a clean E-into-Q-pillar stun or R cancels his spin (R) and locks him for a Brittle combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After his first bruiser item Wukong's E-Q-R clone all-in spikes hard; your Heartsteel/Sunfire makes you tanky enough to W-poke and survive it."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 3 for W (Bellows Breath) so its shield and unstoppable percent-HP exhale blunt his Q-shred trades","Land E into your Q magma pillar for a knock-up, then Brittle-auto and W for a max-HP punish","Hit 6 and bait his ult — your R double knock-up or E-Q stun cancels his spin (R) for a kill"],"foe":["All-in at level 2 with Q armor-shred plus E-dash before your W shield exists","Use the W clone decoy to bait your telegraphed E-Q stun, then re-engage when it's down","Stack armor and a bruiser item to out-duel you in extended even-gold trades"]},"early":"Wukong owns the first two levels here — he has a real level-2 all-in with Q armor-shred and his E-dash gap-close while you have no shield, no combo, and a mana bar that runs dry. Don't contest the early waves; last-hit at range and respect his level-2 spike. The moment you hit 3 and get W (Bellows Breath), the lane stabilizes: its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back through his Q and discourage the E-in all-in.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your window. With a second point in your combo you can punish his E-dash overextensions by dropping a Q magma pillar in his path and E-ing into it for a knock-up, then Brittle-auto and W for a max-HP chunk. Watch the W clone — don't burn your E-Q stun on the decoy. At 6 your R turns his all-in against him: when he spins in with R, your double knock-up or a clean E-Q cancels it and locks him for the kill.","late":"This stays even into the late game. Wukong stacks armor and his first bruiser item gives his E-Q-R clone all-in real burst, but your first tank item (Heartsteel or Sunfire) makes you durable enough to W-poke and tank his combo. Neither of you hard-outscales the other in lane — your edge is teamfights, where your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and a self-comboed E-Q-pillar knock-up into R turn his single-target dive into a liability. Don't get caught alone splitpushing against his clone-juke; group and let your R anchor the fight.","whys":["Wukong's level-2 Q armor-shred plus E-dash all-in beats you while you have no W shield, no combo, and an empty mana bar.","Even level: he can poke with Q but lacks the full burst yet, and you can start farming back toward your level-3 spike.","Your W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its shield and unstoppable percent-HP exhale let you trade back through his Q-shred, evening the lane.","Your second combo point lets you punish his E-dash with an E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and a Brittle-amplified max-HP trade.","Your R double knock-up cancels his spin (R) all-in and chains into E-Q-Brittle for the kill, so you own the 6 window.","His first bruiser item re-arms the E-Q-R clone all-in, but your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike keeps the lane a coinflip you can W-poke through.","Neither champ hard-outscales the other 1v1 — it stays even in lane, and your teamfight ceiling with Masterwork upgrades tips fights, not the duel."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"yasuo","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Yasuo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) online: unstoppable percent-HP exhale that his Windwall cannot block and that applies Brittle for your follow-up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) plus E-into-Q-pillar: a self-comboed double knock-up Windwall can't stop, your hardest all-in window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Heartsteel/Sunfire plus boots: you become a durable W-poke bully who eats his crit autos and trades back through Brittle."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yasuo's biggest window — at 2+ crit items he kites your telegraphed E-Q with double-dash and shreds your armor stacking."}],"wants":{"you":["Land W (Bellows Breath) percent-HP exhale through his Windwall to poke and apply Brittle","Hit E-into-Q-pillar knock-up so his Windwall and dashes cannot deny your CC","Own the 6-to-first-item window with R double knock-up before his crit items come online"],"foe":["Windwall your engage attempts and dash through your minion wave to dodge E","Stack crit items and farm safely to his 2+ item power spike","Use his E dashes to weave through your telegraphed Q-pillar and ult knock-up"]},"early":"Yasuo is a weak laner before items, but so are you at Levels 1-2 — no shield, no combo, mana-starved, so just farm and don't throw a Q he can dash-cancel through the wave. The key fact about this lane: his Windwall (W) blocks projectiles, but your W (Bellows Breath) is a point-blank exhale, not a projectile, so it pokes him for percent-HP and applies Brittle right through his only defensive tool. At Level 3 you stabilize hard — W-poke when he steps to last-hit and back off before his crit-stacked autos add up.","mid":"This is your lane. From 4-5 your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up punishes him when he dashes in on your wave, and his Windwall does nothing against a knock-up. At 6 your R is the takeover: the charging elemental knocks him up, you reactivate to ram a second, bigger knock-up, then W-Brittle and detonate — he can E-dash but he can't escape a self-comboed double CC. Force every all-in here before his crit items arrive.","late":"At 2+ crit items Yasuo flips this — Infinity Edge plus his passive shield and double-dash let him kite your slow, telegraphed E-Q and his crit DPS chews through your armor stacking faster than you Brittle him. His Windwall still doesn't stop your knock-ups, so your value is landing one R to set up your team, not soloing him. Close the game on your first-item bully window; don't try to 1v1 a fed Yasuo in the open.","whys":["Yasuo is weak level 1, but so are you — no shield, no combo, mana-hungry — so nobody owns it; just farm.","His dash-through-minions lets him dodge a level-2 Q, and you still have no W shield to trade back, so it stays even.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online and pokes him for percent-HP through his Windwall while applying Brittle — your first real edge.","A second combo point lets E-into-Q-pillar knock him up when he dashes in, and Windwall cannot block a knock-up.","R double knock-up plus E-Q sets up a self-comboed all-in his dashes and Windwall can't deny — your peak.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a durable W-poke bully before his crit items reclaim the duel.","At 2+ crit items his Infinity Edge DPS and double-dash kite shred your armor stacking and out-duel you — give him the late game."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"yone","win":["Skill","Yone","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Yone"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Yone's Q dash and W cleave let him poke you while you are shieldless and mana-starved — concede the levels and just farm with Q tip."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back through his Q pokes for the first time."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R (Call of the Forge God) double knock-up plus E-into-Q-pillar stun chains Brittle on a target who has to stand still — your hardest all-in before he is itemized."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Yone's third Q and ult mobility let him kite your telegraphed E-Q and reset with E-rewind — the duel slips back to him as a scaler."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive Levels 1-2 farming with Q tip, then trade back with W's unstoppable percent-HP exhale once you hit 3","Land E into your own Q pillar so the knock-up stun lets W apply Brittle for amplified burst","Hit your Level 6 R double knock-up all-in before his items let him kite your combo"],"foe":["Poke you down levels 1-2 with Q dash and W cleave while you have no shield or combo","Dodge your telegraphed E-Q with his third Q dash and reset trades with E spirit-rewind","Scale to 2+ items where his mobility and DPS out-duel your single-target presence"]},"early":"Yone owns the first two levels here because you are one of the worst level-1 toplaners — no shield, no combo, mana-hungry — and his Q dash plus W spirit-cleave let him chip you for free. Don't contest it: last-hit with the tip of your Q and accept the poke. At Level 3 your W (Bellows Breath) flips the tempo — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield mean you can finally trade back through his pokes and he can't simply walk you down.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are roughly even — you can punish an overextended Yone with E into your own Q pillar for a knock-up stun, but his E spirit-rewind lets him undo a bad trade by snapping back to his old position. The key is to not throw E blindly; he'll dash your telegraph with Q. Level 6 is your window: R's charging double knock-up plus E-Q forces him to sit still long enough for W to stack Brittle and burst him before he has the items to escape.","late":"This is where Yone reclaims the lane. At 2+ items his third Q stack, ult gap-close, and E-rewind let him kite your slow, telegraphed E-Q all day and reset any trade he loses. You stop being able to pin him 1v1. Don't force the duel late — your value shifts to teamfights, where your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 and chained R-into-pillar CC make you the anchor while your team handles the slippery Yone.","whys":["You are both weak level 1, but he has a Q dash and W cleave to poke while you have no shield — farm with Q tip and concede it.","Still shieldless and mana-starved, you eat his Q-poke trades; he edges the level-2 window before your W.","W (Bellows Breath) comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP exhale and shield let you trade back evenly through his pokes.","You can punish overextension with E into your Q pillar, but his E spirit-rewind undoes bad trades — it stays even.","R's double knock-up plus E-Q-pillar stun pins him for W's Brittle burst before he is itemized — your clearest all-in.","Your first tank item (Heartsteel/Sunfire) lets you W-poke and tank his cleave, holding the lane edge through itemization.","At 2+ items his third Q, ult mobility and E-rewind kite your telegraphed E-Q — the scaling duelist reclaims the 1v1."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"yorick","win":["Yorick","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Yorick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Yorick's strongest window — his E mist slow + ghouls let him chunk you while you have no shield and no combo, so just farm."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"W (Bellows Breath) comes online: unstoppable percent-HP poke through his ghouls plus a shield that blunts his E-cage all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R double knock-up into E-Q pillar Brittle is your hardest all-in — it kills Yorick before Maiden can swarm and answers a ghost-wall escape."},{"when":"2+ items","text":"Yorick's split takes over: Maiden + ghouls shove and his E-cage zones you off the side wave, so close before he gets two items."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach Level 3 W to poke through his ghoul wall with unstoppable percent-HP and shield off his E-cage commit","Land E into your own Q pillar for the knock-up stun, then W-Brittle and auto for the burst","Use Level 6 R double knock-up to win the all-in before Maiden snowballs his split"],"foe":["Stack ghouls and Maiden to shove you in and free up his side-lane split","Land E (Mourning Mist) to slow you and mark you for ghoul/Maiden focus","Trap you with W ghost-wall when you E in, then cage you out of the wave to deny CS and scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Yorick's window, not yours — you have no shield, no combo, and you are mana-starved, so eat the ghoul poke and his E-slow chip and just hit your last-hits. Do not walk up to trade into a ghoul wall while you still lack W. Once you hit Level 3 and pick up W (Bellows Breath), you stabilize hard: it is unstoppable, shields off his chip, and chunks him with percent-HP fire right through his ghouls.","mid":"This is where you take the lane over. With Q-pillar and a second combo point, E into your own Q wall for the knock-up stun, then W to Brittle him and auto for the bonus damage — his ghouls and Maiden cannot out-trade that. Watch his W ghost-wall: he drops it to trap you mid-dash, so bait it or angle your E so terrain is still on the far side. At 6 your R double knock-up wins the all-in outright and kills him before Maiden arrives.","late":"Yorick is a hard scaler and a splitpush specialist, so the longer this goes the more his Maiden + ghoul wave and E-cage side-lane control beat your single-target presence. Your free Masterwork upgrades at 13 keep your team ahead, but in a straight 1v1 for a side wave at two items he zones you off the CS and out-DPSes you. Close the lane and snowball mid-game; do not try to duel him for a sidelane once he is itemized — group and use your teamfight CC instead.","whys":["You are one of the weakest level-1 toplaners with no shield or combo, while Yorick's E-slow and ghouls let him poke you freely.","Still no shield until W, but he cannot fully commit either — both of you are just farming, so the window is even.","W (Bellows Breath) gives you unstoppable percent-HP poke and a shield that out-trades his ghoul chip and blunts his E-cage all-in.","A second combo point lets you E-into-Q-pillar knock-up and W-Brittle punish, which his ghouls and Maiden cannot answer in a short trade.","R adds a long-range double knock-up that wins the all-in and kills him before Maiden can swarm.","Your first tank/health item plus W-poke makes you a durable lane bully who out-trades his ghoul wall.","Yorick out-scales: Maiden + ghouls and his E-cage take over the side lane, out-DPSing your single-target presence for the wave."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"zac","win":["Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Once you have Q and W, your Bellows Breath unstoppable percent-HP poke chunks his blob HP through every E-sling trade he tries."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Call of the Forge God double knock-up answers his E-Q-W engage outright — you out-CC the engage tank in his own gimmick."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike plus level-13 Masterwork upgrades give your team free gold he can never match as an off-meta pick."},{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"His only window: he can E-sling onto you and Q-knockup before you have W's shield, so don't path into river brush early."}],"wants":{"you":["Land W's Brittle and follow with E-into-Q-pillar knock-up to detonate it for amplified burst","Reach level 6 and use R's double knock-up to blow up his telegraphed E-sling engage","Out-itemize him into teamfights where your free Masterwork upgrades give the whole team a gold lead"],"foe":["Land E-sling engages and chain Q-knockup into W to trade in his favor","Stall lane with passive blob pickups and sustain through your W poke","Roam and use E to gank sidelanes or peel for teammates in skirmishes"]},"early":"Zac is just another tank for your W to chew through, but level 1-2 you have no shield and no combo, so respect his E-sling: if he ranges in from brush he can Q-knockup and W you before you can answer. Sit back and farm to 3. The second you have Bellows Breath, your unstoppable percent-HP exhale shreds his big blob health pool and the shield blunts his all-in — he can't out-trade that with even-damage poke.","mid":"This is where you take over. Bait his E-sling, then E into your own Q-pillar to knock him up and detonate W's Brittle for amplified damage — he has no dash to dodge the wall collision. At 6 your R double knock-up flat-out beats his engage: when he commits E-Q, you ram him for a long knock-up and your CC chain outlasts his. He sustains with blob pickups, so deny them by trading on top of him, not at range.","late":"You keep winning. Zac is an off-meta isolation target — pick him off before a fight starts with E-Q-R and your team collapses. Your level-13 Masterwork upgrades hand your whole team an effective gold lead he simply can't match as a weaker-curve pick, and your self-comboed CC sets up every kill without needing him to over-extend. Just don't let him E-sling onto your carry first in a chaotic fight.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and are mana-starved at 1 — but Zac is a slow tank too, so just farm and dodge his E-sling from brush.","Still pre-W you can't punish, and his E-Q-W engage can chunk you, so concede the level and last-hit safely.","Bellows Breath comes online — its unstoppable percent-HP poke and shield out-trade his even-damage blob pokes.","Your E-into-Q-pillar knock-up detonates W's Brittle for burst he has no dash to dodge.","R's double knock-up out-CCs his entire E-Q engage — you own the all-in at 6.","Your Heartsteel/Sunfire spike makes you a durable W-poke bully he can't sustain against.","Your free Masterwork upgrades give your team a gold lead and you isolate the off-meta Zac before fights even start."]},
  {"a":"ornn","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Skill","Ornn","Ornn","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 1-2","text":"Ziggs sits past your W range and chunks you with Bouncing Bomb while you have no shield or combo to answer — just farm and eat it."},{"when":"Lvl 3","text":"Q-pillar plus E gives you a wall to block his bombs and a self-knockup, so you can finally trade back through his poke if he steps up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R into E-Q knock-up is a long-range engage that punishes a stationary Ziggs — your one window to delete him before he gets Lich/Liandry's."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-build Ziggs out-ranges your whole kit and siege-pokes you off objectives — get on top of him with R or stay tanky and eat the bombs for your carries."}],"wants":{"you":["Use your Q magma pillar to body-block his Bouncing Bomb line and deny the poke","Land R into E-Q-pillar knock-up to close the gap and burst him before he peels","Farm safely with Q to level 6, then convert every Ziggs misstep into an all-in"],"foe":["Poke you down with Bouncing Bomb from outside your W and E range every wave","Zone you off the wave and objectives with his Satchel Charge knockback and E minefield","Scale to Liandry's/Lich Bane and siege you out without ever entering your combo range"]},"early":"Ziggs out-ranges everything you have at level 1 — you have no shield, no combo, no mana, and his Bouncing Bomb chunks you while you walk up to last-hit. Don't try to fight it; just farm with Q from max range and accept the poke. Once you hit 3 and have Q plus W, you can drop your magma pillar to physically wall off his bomb line and use W's unstoppable shield to soak a trade if he over-pokes.","mid":"Levels 4-5 are about disrespecting his poke with your pillar: place Q terrain between you and him so his Bouncing Bomb and minefield lose their angle, and look for an E-into-pillar knock-up if he steps up to shove. At 6 your R is the equalizer — a long-range double knock-up that lets you close the gap his whole kit is built to keep. Bait his Satchel Charge (W) knockback, then R-engage into E-Q the instant it's on cooldown.","late":"This is where Ziggs reclaims it. Full-build artillery out-ranges your entire kit and siege-pokes you off every objective, and you'll never reach him in a straight line — your telegraphed E-Q is too slow for him to ever stand in. Your job flips from dueling to anchoring: build pure tank, use your free Masterwork upgrades to fund your carries, and either flank with R or simply body-block his bombs so your team gets on top of him. Don't chase him solo — he kites your knock-up forever.","whys":["You have no shield, no combo and no mana at level 1 while his Bouncing Bomb pokes you from outside your W range — concede and farm.","Still no answer to his ranged bombs at 2; he zones you off the wave with E minefield and Satchel knockback while you just last-hit.","Your Q magma pillar and W shield finally let you wall his bomb line and trade back — even footing if he over-extends to poke.","Your E-into-pillar knock-up punishes him for stepping up to shove, but he can poke safely if he respects it — genuinely skill-based.","R adds a long-range double knock-up that closes the gap his whole kit exists to keep, so you own the all-in before his AP items.","Your first tank item plus W's percent-HP poke makes you durable enough to walk through his bombs and threaten the 6 combo again.","Full-build artillery out-ranges your entire kit and siege-pokes you off objectives — you anchor and tank for your team instead of dueling."]}
